Abstract: This paper is intended to report to the people of Laos the nature of the United States response to the Government's requests for assistance and to indicate the scope of the current United States aid program to Laos.  All of the measures reported in this paper are carefully integrated into the plans of the Royal Lao Government and are carried out under the supervision of the appropriate ministries of the Government. Abstract: Project to enable the Government of El Salvador to conduct a 3-year regionally coordinated malaria eradication program.  The program will consist of an intensive collective drug campaign to reduce the number of human carriers of the disease, and a continuation of spraying operations in pertinent areas to prevent transmission of the disease. Epidemiological surveillance, including mass hematic sampling, will be maintained to evaluate disease incidence, develop a case treatment strategy, and guide corollary preventative measures.

Abstract: This report is one of twenty-three country studies conducted as part of the worldwide survey of returned participants in accordance with AID/W instructions and guidelines contained in ICATO Circular A-175, November 1959.  The major purpose of this global effort was to obtain an overview of how the participant training program was progressing to ascertain ways in which future training might be effective at the country, AID/W, and training institution levels.  The study involved oral interviews in 1961 with 605 returned participants in the Japanese Productivity Study Team, a random sample from 2555 returnees. This was a highly successful program geared specificially to sending short-term productivity teams of 8-12 peoples to the U.S. for specialized training. The report has no generally applicable recommendations.  (Participant training abstract)

Abstract: The National Development Reference Library was conceived by the Agency for International Development to provide a working reference tool in developing countries for planers and executives of programs of social and economic growth and change.  The collection, which provides information on the application of human and physical resources to the processes of national growth, has been limited almost entirely to U.S. publications.  Subjects range from theories of development planning to village improvement case studies.  Titles were selected for the most part for their value to the generalist practitioner, rather than to the specialist or expert. (Excerpt)

Abstract: USAID PROVIDES LOAN TO GUANABARA STATE SANITATION DEPARTMENT (SURSAN), BRAZILIAN PUBLIC UTILITY, TO IMPROVE SEWER SYSTEM OPERATIONS AND MAINTENANCE AND TO HELP PROVIDE SEWER SERVICE THROUGHOUT HEAVILY URBANIZED STATE, AS CALLED FOR IN 1962 STATE MASTER PLAN. PROJECT PROVIDES NECESSARY EQUIPMENT AND CONSULTING SERVICES TO ASSIST DEPARTMENT OF SANITATION (DES) IN SURSAN MEET DEMANDS OF URBAN POPULATION AND TO COMPLEMENT PREVIOUS SEWER CONSTRUCTION AND EXPANSION PROGRAM. LOAN COVERS COST OF COMMODITIES, TRAINING, AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. SPECIALIZED US MAINTENANCE EQUIPMENT IS PROVIDED TO CLEAN SEWER LINES. FINANCE DEPARTMENT ACQUIRES BURROUGHS B-200 DIGITAL COMPUTER TO IMPROVE BILLING PROCEDURES. KEY PERSONNEL STUDY COMPUTERIZED SYSTEMS IN US. WATER COMPANY SHARES COMPUTER USE AND SUPPLIES PAPER AND BILL COLLECTION SERVICE. MOSQUITO CONTROL EQUIPMENT PERMITS EXPANSION OF CONTROL OPERATIONS OVER ENTIRE STATE. DIRECTOR OF INSECT AND RODENT CONTROL DIVISION STUDIES ADMINISTRATIVE AND TECHNICAL ASPECTS OF MOSQUITO CONTROL PROGRAMS. NEW TELECOMMUNICATIONS EQUIP ALLOWS DES TO USE ITS MOBILE MAINTENANCE UNITS EFFECTIVELY FOR IMPROVED SERVICE. SPECIALIZED LAB EQUIPMENT IS USED TO DETERMINE EFFECTIVENESS OF SEWAGE TREATMENT IN ELIMINATING POLLUTION BEFORE DISCHARGE INTO OCEAN. FEASIBILITY STUDY IS MADE OF SUBMARINE OUTFALL (UNDERWATER DISCHARGE AT SEA) DISPOSAL SYSTEM. CONCENTRATED 2-YEAR TRAINING PROGRAM SUPERVISED BY USAID/BRAZIL WATER AND SEWER SPECIALISTS TEACHES PERSONNEL TO USE NEW EQUIPMENT. ENGINEERS AND TECHNICIANS ARE TRAINED TO USE MODERN SEWER MAINTENANCE EQUIPMENT. US CONSULTING FIRM STUDIES FEASIBILITY OF IMPROVED SEWAGE DISPOSAL FACILITIES, INCLUDING DEEP-SEA FACILITY. USAID PROVIDES LOAN FOR EQUIPMENT AND TECHNICAL CONSULTANT SERVICES. SURSAN CONTRIBUTES ADDITIONAL EQUIPMENT, INSTALLATION COST, COST OF TRAINING PROGRAM. PROJECT RESULTS IN REDUCED INCIDENCE OF WATER-BORNE DISEASE AND IN IMPROVED SERVICES FOR EXISTING INDUSTRIES. PROJECT 5120239 IS FUNDED IN SAME CAP.
Personal Author: PRINDIVILLE, J. M.|HUDSON, LEVERNE D.|et al.

Abstract: LOAN PROVIDED TO THE CORPORACION NICARAGUENSE DE INVERSIONES (CNI) TO PROMOTE THE CREATION, EXPANSION, AND MORE EFFECTIVE OPERATION OF PRIVATE ENTERPRISES, PRIMARILY IN NICARAGUA, AND TO A CERTAIN EXTENT IN THE OTHER MEMBER COUNTRIES OF THE CENTRAL AMERICAN COMMON MARKET. CNI, A PRIVATE INTERMEDIATE CREDIT INSTITUTION WITH OFFICES IN MANAGUA, WILL EXTEND SUBLOANS TO THE PRIVATE SECTOR (INCLUDING INDUSTRIAL, AGRICULTURAL, TRANSPORTATION, AND OTHER ENTERPRISES) AT MEDIUM AND LONG TERMS (3 TO 15 YEARS) AT AN INTEREST RATE OF 10%. CNI WILL ALSO MAKE EQUITY INVESTMENTS AND CONTINUE ITS CO-SIGNING OPERATION BY OFFERING ITS "ENDORSEMENT AND GUARANTY TO PAY" TO A FOREIGN CREDITOR OF A NICARAGUAN CLIENT. ALL POTENTIAL  SUBPROJECTS WILL BE THOROUGHLY INVESTIGATED AND RESEARCHED BY CNI STAFF BEFORE A LOAN IS GRANTED OR AN INVESTMENT MADE. AFTER APPROVAL, CNI WILL SCRUTINIZE THE CONDUCT OF THE RECIPIENT AND PROVIDE REMEDIAL ADVICE WHERE NEEDED. THIS PROJECT CONTINUES THE CNI LENDING AND INVESTMENT PROGRAM BEGUN UNDER THE FIRST LOAN FROM USAID (5240550) WHICH WAS SIGNED 5/25/65. THE PROCEEDS OF THIS SECOND LOAN WILL BE USED WITH INCREASING EMPHASIS ON THE CREATION OF NEW ENTERPRISES AND MAY BE USED ONLY FOR THE PROCUREMENT OF GOODS AND SERVICES FROM THE US.

Abstract: LOAN TO GOVERNMENT OF IRAN WILL PAY COSTS OF TECHNICAL ASSISTANCEANCE IN MANAGEMENT,OPERATIONS,TRAINING EQUIPMENT,TRAINING AND FEASIBILITY STUDIES NEEDED TO IMPROVE AND EXPAND IRAN'S NATIONAL PROGRAM IN ELECTRIC POWER DEVELOPMENT. TECHNICAL ASSIST WILL BE PROVIDED BY HARZA ENGINEERING CO AND OTHER US CONSULTANTS WHO WILL WORK ON THE JOB WITH COUNTERPARTS IN REGIONAL UTILITY CO'S (RUC'S) AND MINISTRY OF WATER AND POWER (MWP),ASSISTING IN STAFF TRAINING AND DAILY ADMINISTRATION. CONSULTANTS WILL SET UP CENTRAL ORGANIZATION IN MWP CAPABLE OF ASSISTING RUC'S IN MANAGEMENT,ACCOUNTING AND OPERATIONS; ORGANIZE EACH RUC; FORMULATE POLICIES AND METHODS OF UTILITY OPERATIONS THAT STANDARDIZE RUC PROCEDURES; INSTITUTE UNIFORM ACCOUNTING SYSTEMS IN RUC'S; PREPARE JOB EVALUATION AND POSITION QUALIFICATION STANDARDS; PREPARE SPECIFICATIONS AND ESTIMATES OF SECONDARY PROJECTS NOT CONTEMPLATED IN IRAN'S ELECTRIFICATION PLANS; FORMULATE POLICIES ON PUBLIC AND CUSTOMER RELATIONS; EVALUATE EQUIPMENT PURCHASE BIDS; PREPARE ANNUAL OPERATING AND CONSTRUCTION BUDGETS IN ACCORDANCE WITH UNIFORM AND APPROVED STANDARDS. CONSULTANTS WILL PERFORM FEASIBILITY STUDIES THAT EVALUATE CURRENT AND FUTURE ECONOMIC AND PHYSICAL NEEDS,FACILITIES AND PROCEDURES FOR ADEQUATE COMMUNICATION,INCLUDING TELE-METERING,TO ACCOMPLISH ECONOMIC LOADING OF GENERATING CAPACITY AND TO PROVIDE CONTINUITY OF SERVICE REQUIRED BY CUSTOMERS,INCLUDING EVALUATION OF VOLTAGE AND FREQUENCY CONTROL. CONSULTANTS WILL ALSO DEVELOP A TRAINING PROGRAM FOR EXECUTIVES,ACCOUNTANTS,POWER PLANT OPERATORS, LINE MEN, ELECTRICIANS, AND MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL AND DEVELOP SAFETY PRACTICES. CONSULTANTS ATTACHED TO MWP WILL COORDINATE THE WORK OF TEAMS ATTACHED TO RUC'S. THE ELEMENT OF INSTRUCTION WILL DOMINATE ALL CONSULTANTS WORK WITH THE AIM OF EVENTUAL TRAINEE SELF-SUFFICIENCY.

Abstract: LOAN TO THE GOVT OF NICARAGUA FOR THE CONSTRUCTION OF AN ANTICIPATED 114 PRIMARY SCHOOLS (OF A 6-CLASSROOM TYPE) AT URBAN AN SEMI-URBAN SITES.  LOAN WILL FINANCE 50% OF TOTAL PROJECT COSTS. THE BULK WILL BE USED FOR CONSTRUCTION COSTS AND THE REMAINDER FOR A CONTRACT WITH A NICARAGUAN ENGINEERING/MANAGEMENT FIRM TO SUPERVISE AND  ADMINISTER THE CONSTRUCTION. GON WILL PROVIDE FURNISHINGS AND EQUIPMENT FOR THE SCHOOLS AND COMPLEMENTARY FUNDING FOR THEIR CONSTRUCTION.  THE URBAN AND SEMI-URBAN COMMUNITIES SELECTED AS SITES FOR THE SCHOOLS WILL PROVIDE LAND, LABOR, MATERIALS, AND MONEY FOR THIS PROJECT AS A "SELF-HELP" CONTRIBUTION. THE CONSTRUCCIONES NACIONALES (CN), A DIVISION OF THE GON'S MINISTRY OF PUBLIC WORKS WILL BE FULLY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE CONSTRUCTION PROGRAM.  GRANTING THE DOMINANT ROLE TO CN IS INTENDED TO DEVELOP WITHIN THIS AGENCY THE CAPACITY TO PLAN AND DIRECT SIMILAR FUTURE PROGRAMS.  DETAILED ENGINEERING PLANS FOR THE BUILDINGS WERE PREPARED AND THE BUILDING SITES SELECTED PRIOR TO PROJECT.  CN WILL CONTRACT THE AFOREMENTIONED NICARAGUAN ENGINEERING/MANAGEMENT FIRM TO: PREPARE THE OF OPERATIONS; ASSIST IN BID SOLICITATION AND AWARDING OF CONSTRUCTION CONTRACTS; CERTIFY READINESS OF THE SITES FOR CONSTRUCTION; SCHEDULE ORDERS AND ALLOCATE CONSTRUCTION MATERIALS; SUPERVISE CONSTRUCTION; MAINTAIN COST ACCOUNTS AND RECORDS; CERTIFY CONTRACTOR PROGRESS PAYMENTS; AND RECOMMEND COMPLETED SCHOOLS FOR ACCEPTANCE AND FINAL CONTRACTOR PAYMENTS. COSTS FOR THESE SERVICES IN EXCESS OF THE AID-LOAN FUNDED AMOUNT WILL BE PROVIDED FOR BY THE GON.

Abstract: MAY 1966 INITIAL AUDIT OF AID CONTRIBUTION TO PERNAMBUCO HOUSING PROJ, RECIFE, BRAZIL, COVERS PERIOD FROM INCEPTION THROUGH 12/31/65. USAID/B CONTRIBUTED 200 MILLION CRUZEIROS FROM PL 480, TITLE I, CRUZEIRO GRANT FUNDS, IN CONCURRENCE WITH THE COORDINATING COMMISSION FOR THE ALLIANCE FOR PROGRESS, TO THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO FOR THE CONSTRUCTION OF 700 HOUSING UNITS IN THE ALTO DO JORDAO & IBURA DISTRICTS. THE HOUSES WERE TO BE SOLD TO SKILLED LABOR & LOW-SALARIED OFFICE WORKERS WITH PROCEEDS USED FOR ADDITIONAL HOUSING CONSTRUCTION. PROJ WAS DESIGNED TO COMPLEMENT EFFORTS OF THE STATE HOUSING AGENCY (SSCM) TO DEAL WITH INCREASINGLY ACUTE URBAN CONGESTION. AUDITORS EXAMINED PERTINENT RECORDS & DOCUMENTS,MET WITH OFFICIALS,AND MADE A FIELD TRIP TO THE HOUSING AREA,INTERVIEWING 40 NEW-HOME OWNERS. A TOTAL OF 690 HOUSES WERE CONSTRUCTED INITIALLY WITH 44 BUILT SUBSEQUENTLY FROM SALE PROCEEDS. AUDITORS FOUND THE HOUSES GENERALLY ATTRACTIVE AND WELL CONSTRUCTED,THOUGH SOME COMPLAINTS ABOUT CRACKS IN WALLS WERE NOTED. ENVIRONMENTAL DEFICIENCIES WERE APPARENT,HOWEVER: ERODED DIRT STREETS,THE LACK OF ADEQUATE COMMERCIAL & COMMUNITY FACILITIES,AND PROTRACTED DELAY IN THE INSTALLATION OF A WATER SYSTEM IN THE IBURA COMMUNITY DUE TO INTERDEPARTMENTAL DISPUTES. AUDITORS FOUND RESIDENTS TO BE MEMBERS OF THE SPECIFIED ECON STRATA DESPITE EVIDENCE OF PREFERENCE BASED ON POLITICAL AFFILIATION AND PURCHASE FOR INVESTMENT PURPOSES. EXAMINATION REVEALED PROPER DISBURSEMENT AND USE OF USAID FUNDS AND FULL EXPENDITURES OF SSCM & PERNAMBUCO STATE FUNDS,BUT INCOMPLETE ACCOUNTING. AUDITORS RECOMMEND THAT USAID REQUEST THAT SSCM RETURN INTEREST ACCRUED ON THE USAID DISBURSEMENT IN LINE WITH A RECENT US CONTROLLER GENERAL RULING; THAT SSCM ALSO RETURN 2.135 MILLION UNEXPENDED CRUZEIROS; AND THAT SSCM SUPPLY NECESSARY DISBURSEMENT DETAILS SO THAT USAID ACCOUNTING RECORDS MIGHT BE COMPLETED. AUDITORS,UPON DISCOVERING THAT SIGNS INDICATING ALLIANCE FOR PROGRESS PARTICIPATION HAD BEEN RIPPED DOWN AND USED FOR LUMBER BY THE PROJECT'S IMPOVERISHED NEIGHBORS,RECOMMEND THAT USAID DETERMINE THE FEASIBILITY OF ERECTING NEW SIGNS.

Abstract: LOAN PROVIDED TO THE GOVERNMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA (ROKG) WILL FINANCE THE FOREIGN EXCHANGE COSTS OF MODERN CIVIL AIR NAVIGATION EQUIPMENT, COMMUNICATIONS FACILITIES, AND RELATED SAFETY EQUIPMENT AT KIMPO INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT (SEOUL), AT PUSAN INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, ALONG ENROUTE AIRWAYS, AND AT OTHER DOMESTIC AIRPORTS (CHEJU, KANGNUNG, POHANG, TAEJON, KWANGJU, AND SAMCHOK). LOAN WILL ALSO FINANCE TECHNICAL ADVISORY SERVICES, SUPERVISORY ENGINEERING SERVICES, AND PROCUREMENT SERVICES BY THE US FEDERAL AVIATION ADMINISTRATION (FAA). PROJECT WILL BE IMPLEMENTED BY THE ROKG CIVIL AVIATION BUREAU (CAB). A NEW AVIATION CONSTRUCTION BUREAU WILL BE ESTABLISHED WITHIN THE CAB TO PROVIDE THE ENGINEERING AND CONSTRUCTION CAPABILITY NECESSARY FOR LOAN IMPLEMENTATION CAB STAFF WILL BE INCREASED FROM 111 TO 282 TO ADEQUATELY OPERATE AND MAINTAIN THE EXPANDED AIRWAYS SYSTEM. THE FAA TECHNICIANS WILL SUPERVISE A TRAINING PROGRAM FOR CAB STAFF WHICH WILL INVOLVE THE PARTICIPATION OF THE ROK NATIONAL AVIATION COLLEGE. LOAN WILL FINANCE US TRAINING OF 15 CAB TECHNICIANS IN EQUIPMENT MAINTENANCE AT THE FAA AERONAUTICAL CENTER IN OKLAHOMA CITY. LOAN-FINANCED EQUIPMENT WILL INCLUDE 1 AIRPORT SURVEILLANCE RADAR SYSTEM, 1 SECONDARY SURVEILLANCE RADAR SYSTEM, 4 VERY HIGH FREQUENCY OMNI-DIRECTIONAL RADIO RANGES (VOR), 4 TACTICAL AIR NAVIGATION AIDS (TO BE CO-LOCATED WITH VOR'S), 3 INSTRUMENT LANDING SYSTEMS, 2 VISUAL APPROACH SLOPE INDICATING SYSTEMS, 1 SELECTIVE CALLING SYSTEM, AND 1 RUNWAY/TAXIWAY LIGHTING SYSTEM. OTHER SUPPLEMENTAL AND SUPPORT EQUIPMENT WILL INCLUDE IMPROVED AERONAUTICAL TELECOMMUNICATIONS; FIRE-FIGHTING, RESCUE, AND AIRPORT MAINTENANCE EQUIPMENT AND VEHICLES; ROTATING LIGHT BEACONS; AND WIND TEES. RELATED CIVIL CONSTRUCTION WILL INCLUDE ROADS, BUILDINGS, CABLES AND DUCT LINES, POWER LINES, ANTENNA STRUCTURES, APPROACH LIGHT TOWERS, POWER GENERATORS, AND SWITCHGEAR. THE IMPROVED SYSTEMS WILL ENABLE ROKG TO MEET THE STANDARDS OF THE INTERNATIONAL CIVIL AVIATION ORGANIZATION, THEREBY FULFILLING ROKG'S RESPONSIBILITIES FOR THE SAFE OPERATION OF AIR TRAFFIC AND AIRPORTS WITHIN ITS FLIGHT INFORMATION REGION.

Abstract: EVALUATES (APRIL 30, 1965-MARCH 7, 1966) RESOURCES SURVEY PROJECT TO LOCATE AREAS OF AGR'L POTENTIAL MOST SUITABLE FOR  SETTLEMENT IN INTERIOR OF BRAZIL, TO RCMND ALTERNATE LAND USES AND METHODS OF SOIL MGMT FOR SUSTAINED PRODUCTION, AND TO TRAIN COMPETENT SOIL SURVEY WORKERS IN MINISTRY OF AGRICULTURE (MOA). EVALUATOR PARTICIPATED IN PROGRESS BRIEFINGS, MAR 7-8, 1966, AND IN VISITS TO RIO DE JANERIO (MAR 8-APR 1 AND MAY 2-26, 1966). EVALUATOR ASSISTED BRAZILIANS TO DEVELOP ANNUAL PLAN OF SOIL SURVEY OPS, FORMAT FOR SOIL REPORTS, AND PRINCIPLES AND CRITERIA FOR SOIL SURVEY INTRPRTATN. PLAN OF OPS INCLUDED TRNG OF NEW PEDOLOGISTS,SELECTING PRIORITY AREAS FOR RECONSNCE MAPPING WITH ESTABMT OF MAPPING GOALS AND DEVELPMT OF SOIL SURVEY INTRPRTATNS. PLAN ALSO INCLUDED DEVELPMT OF PLAN FOR SYSTEMATIC SAMPLING OF SOILS IN EACH RECONSNCE AREA,INITIATING COLLECTN & CLASSIFICTN OF INFO ON EACH AREA,DEVLPG SYSTEM OF FIELD REVIEWS AND INSPECTNS TO EVALUATE PROGRESS AND EFCTVNESS OF TRNG AND FIELD MAPPING,INCREASING USE OF OPS MGMT TECHNIQUES. COLLECTN AND DISMNATN OF SOIL SURVEY DATA,MAPS AND PHOTOS FROM A CENTRAL POINT IS RCMNDED,WITH PUBLICATN OF TECHNICAL WORK AND MAPS. EVALAUTOR EXPLORED TECHNIQUES OF STUDYING SOILS AND AGR IN THE AMAZON BASIN (MAY 8-18,1966),CONFIRMED OR MODIFIED BOUNDARY LINES ON EXPLORATORY SOILS MAP,AND CONDUCTED INTERVIEWS WITH FARMERS AND TECHNCNS. SCHEMATIC SOILS MAP COVERING 2/3 OF BRAZIL IS NEARLY COMPLETE,AND IS USED TO ESTAB PRIORITY OF AREAS FOR RECONSNCE SOIL SURVEY FOR AGR DEVEL. PROJECT HAS COMPLETED 2-MO SOIL SURVEY TRNG COURSE FOR 42 RECENT GRADS OF BRAZIL'S AGR COLLEGE. EVALR RCMNDS THAT FUTURE CLASSRM TRNG BE CONDUCTED BY UNIV AT KM47,THAT 2 SOIL ADVISORS WITH EXPERTISE IN SOIL SURVEY WORK AND IN SOIL INTERPRETATN BE ASSIGNED TO PROJ FOR 2 YRS. DELAYS IN GETTING ESSENTIAL EQUIPMT & SUPPLIES SHOULD BE REDUCED. EMPHASIS SHOULD BE SHIFTED TO PROGRAMMNG,ORGANIZNG,SCHEDULNG SOIL SURVEYS. EVALAUTOR RECOMMNDS ADDING SPECIALISTS IN FORESTRY,ECONOMICS,HYDROLOGY,CROP/GRASSLANDS MGMT,ETC; ALSO RECOMMENDS US TRNG FOR 1/2 BRAZILIANS IN PUBLIC ADMIN AS APPLIED TO RESOURCES DEVELOPMENT & CONSERVATION.

Abstract: PROJECT TO HELP BRAZIL'S MINISTRY OF EDUCATION TO DEVELOP A PLANNING PROCESS ENABLING BRAZILIAN AUTHORITIES TO PREPARE AND EXECUTE PROGRAMS AIMED AT MEETING THE COUNTRY'S RAPIDLY INCREASING HIGHER EDUCATION NEEDS.  THE PROJECT EXAMINES THE CONDITIONS OF BRAZILIAN HIGHER EDUCATION, DEVELOPS A COMPREHENSIVE PLAN FOR ITS IMPROVEMENT, MAKES RECOMMENDATIONS ON REFORM AND RESTRUCTURING OF BRAZIL'S HIGHER EDUCATION SYSTEM, AND TRAINS CORPS OF BRAZILIAN EDUCATIONAL PLANNERS WHOSE EXPERIENCE AND TRAINING WITH U.S. TEAM WILL ENABLE THEM TO CARRY EDUCATIONAL PLANNING FORWARD ON A CONTINUING BASIS.  THE MIDWEST UNIVERSITIES CONSORTIUM FOR INTERNATIONAL ACTIVITIES (MUCIA) IS CONTRACTED BY A.I.D. TO PROVIDE A 5-PERSON TEAM TO WORK WITH 5 APPOINTED BRAZILIAN EDUCATORS IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF A PLANNING CAPACITY. MUCIA WILL SUBCONTRACT THE UNIVERSITY OF WISCONSIN TO PROVIDE MANAGEMENT, SECRETARIAL, CLERICAL, ACCOUNTING AND AUDITING SERVICES AND TO RECRUIT OVERSEAS PERSONNEL.  U.S. ASSISTANCE INCLUDES PASA SERVICES, CONTRACT SERVICES, LOCAL PERSONNEL COSTS, COMMODITIES AND PARTICIPANT TRAINING.

Abstract: IN 1962 THE UNIVERSITY OF MICHIGAN RECEIVED A USAID GRANT TO EXPLORE THE POTENTIAL OF FOAM PLASTICS FOR SOLVING HOUSING PROBLEMS IN DEVELOPING NATIONS. A FEASIBILITY STUDY COMPLETED IN 1962 ESTABLISHED THE DESIRABILITY OF INVESTIGATING THE USE OF FOAM PLASTICS AS STRUCTURAL MATERIAL. THE PROJECT WAS CONDUCTED IN TWO PHASES. THE FIRST PHASE INVOLVED EXPERIMENTATION TO OBTAIN INFORMATION ON A VARIETY OF FOAM PLASTICS. SEVERAL STRUCTURAL SYSTEMS WERE ESTABLISHED AS SCALE MODELS BEFORE TWO STRUCTURAL CONCEPTS WERE SELECTED FOR FULL-SCALE CONSTRUCTION AND TESTING. ONE CONCEPT INVOLVED APPLICATION OF SPRAY POLYURETHANE FOAM ON A FOLDING WOOD LATTICE ARMATURE. THE OTHER CONCEPT INVOLVED PRODUCTION OF LARGE STRUCTURAL COMPONENTS MADE OF PAPER-LAMINATED POLYURETHANE FOAM BOARD. DURING THE SECOND PHASE OF THE PROJECT, FOUR PROTOTYPE STRUCTURES REPRESENTING DIFFERENT TECHNIQUES WERE BUILT. ONE CONSISTED OF SEVEN UMBRELLA-SHAPED COMPONENTS MADE OF SPRAYED POLYURETHANE FOAM. A SECOND WAS A TWO-STORY STRUCTURE MADE OF TRIANGULATED BENTS OF FOLDED PAPER-LAMINATED POLYURETHANE FOAM BOARD. A THIRD CONSISTED OF FOUR SQUARE UMBRELLA-SHAPED COMPONENTS MADE OF FLEXIBLE FOAM COATED WITH REINFORCED POLYESTER. THE FOURTH WAS A ROOM-SIZE UNIT IN WHICH POLYURETHANE FOAM BOARD SERVED AS THE MANDREL FOR FILAMENT-WOUND POLYESTER. THE RESEARCH PROGRAM ALSO INVESTIGATED REQUIREMENTS FOR PRODUCTION AND MARKETING OF CHEMICALS AND FOAM PLASTIC PRODUCTS FOR STRUCTURES AND BUILDING COMPONENTS IN UNDER DEVELOPED COUNTRIES. THE MAJOR RECOMMENDATION STEMMING FROM THE PROJECT WAS THAT AID COLLABORATE WITH THE U.S. PLASTICS INDUSTRY IN SPONSORING CONSTRUCTION AND EVALUATION OF SUITABLE PROTOTYPE DWELLING UNITS IN DEVELOPING COUNTRIES.

Abstract: Institutionalization is a result of the extent to which specified organizational variables realistically take account of elements in the related environment. This hypothesis guided the attempt to study how a faculty of education in a new university has come to be prized or disprised. Institutionality is not only a matter of what professional educators think and feel; it is a matter of what the new generation of teachers think; what the politicians and kingmakers accept, except, and reward; it is a matter of what its own immediate offspring feel and think about their parent. This study concerns the institutionalization of the program on professional education at a new university in Eastern Nigeria, the extent to which this program has become valued, and to what one may attribute its success or failure in becoming valued. The time span is the first five and one half years in the history of the independent nation and of the college studied. Available in microfiche only.

Abstract: EVALUATES PROJECT TO STRENGTHEN THE PHILIPPINES VOCATIONAL EDUCATION SYSTEM AND IMPROVE THE PHYSICAL FACILITIES DESTROYED DURING WORLD WAR II. EVALUATION COVERS THE PERIOD 7/1/59-12/31/65 AND IS BASED ON STANDARD AUDIT PROCEDURES AND INSPECTION OF USAID-FINANCED SCHOOL EQUIPMENT. THE MISSION PROVIDED $6,779,601 IN TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE, COMMODITIES AND PARTICIPANT TRAINING; AND A COUNTERPART FUND PROVIDED 9,262,977 PESOS UNDER 10 COUNTERPART AGREEMENTS TO REHABILITATE TRADE, INDUSTRIAL. AND AGRICULTURAL SCHOOLS AND TRAIN VOCATIONAL TEACHERS. THE GOVERNMENT OF THE PHILIPPINES CONTRIBUTED 7,770,822 PESOS TO DEFRAY THE TRAINING FACILITIES, CONSTRUCTION, AND EQUIPMENT COSTS. OVERALL COMPLIANCE WITH PROJECT AGREEMENTS WAS FOUND TO BE SATISFACTORY. PROCUREMENT AND USE OF COMMODITIES WERE ADEQUATELY CONTROLLED, AND BUILDINGS CONSTRUCTED WERE BEING USED FOR THE INTENDED PURPOSE AND WERE BEING PROPERLY MAINTAINED. ACCOUNTING AND PROPERTY RECORDS WERE ADEQUATELY KEPT. PARTICIPANT TRAINEES HAD FULFILLED THEIR TRAINING OBLIGATIONS, AND TECHNICAL SERVICES RENDERED COMPLIED WITH CONTRACTUAL AGREEMENTS. HOWEVER, CASH ADVANCES TOTALLING 33,782 PESOS FROM SIX COUNTERPART AGREEMENTS WERE FOUND TO BE OUTSTANDING. EVEN AFTER FOUR YEARS FROM PROJECT COMPLETION, THIS SUM HAS STILL NOT BEEN TRANSFERRED TO THE COUNTERPART FUND SPECIAL ACCOUNT. IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT THE PHILIPPINE ECONOMIC COUNCIL INSTRUCT THE PROJECT OFFICIALS OR THE ADMINISTERING BUREAU OF VOCATIONAL EDUCATION TO COLLECT AND REMIT THE BALANCE OF CASH ADVANCES TO THE COUNTERPART FUND SPECIAL ACCOUNT. A SPECIAL AUDIT WILL BE SCHEDULED TO REVIEW ALL OUTSTANDING CASH ADVANCES FOR CLOSED PROJECTS AND TO DETERMINE THE CAUSE OF THIS CONDITION. ALL RECOMMENDATIONS IN 20 PREVIOUS AUDIT REPORTS REVIEWING COMMODITY DISTRIBUTION AND COUNTERPART DISBURSEMENTS WERE IMPLEMENTED AND CONSIDERED CLOSED.

Abstract: Evaluates project to provide financial assistance to the University of the Philippines (UP) to improve and expand its educational facilities. Evaluation covers the period 5/31/51-12/31/65 and was based on standard audit procedures, physical inspection of project-financed commodities, and visits to construction sites. As a result of the project, UP educational facilities and programs were improved.  A total of 123 UP staff received, or are currently receiving, participant training; the remaining two participants departed for training during this evaluation.  UP staff and faculty received average salary increases amounting to 33% over 1961 baseline figures.  A total of 118 faculty residences were completed, 22 units are under construction, and funding is available for 61 additional units.  A music auditorium, and a physical education building and physical plant were constructed.  Sites are currently being prepared for the construction of student dormitories.  Reorganization of administrative procedures is virtually complete.  The project was extended six months; it is anticipated that all funds will be obligated and that UP will be able to continue its operation without external assistance. Contract agreements were fulfilled by participant trainees, construction contractors, and the Government of the Philippines (GOP). However, the audit revealed discrepancies in inventory records kept by UP for dollar-procured commodities, unauthorized disposal of these commodities, and lack of use of equipment in excess of $26,000.  The following recommendations are made to remedy these situations:  (1) UP should conduct an inventory of all dollar-procured commodities on hand. Inventory results should be reconciled with USAID and the GOP, and the loss of any item should be charged to UP. (2) Equipment not in use should be declared nonessential to the project and transferrred to the GOP agencies which have need of them.  (3) Proceeds from the sale of an automobile which were placed erroneously in the UP General Fund should be transferred to the Counterpart Fund Special Account.

Abstract: EVALUATES USAID ASSISTANCE TO THE GOVT OF THE PHILIPPINES FROM 11/01/66-11/30/66 TO UNDERTAKE SURVEYS AND STUDIES PREPARATORY TO THE FORMULATION OF COMPREHENSIVE DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS FOR THE NATION'S SEVEN MAJOR RIVER BASINS. THE CENTRAL LUZON, CAGAYAN, COTABATO AND AUGSAN BASIN REPORTS ARE IN FINAL REPRODUCTION. THE PRELIMINARY REPORT FOR THE BICOL RIVER BASIN IS BEING REVIEWED, AND THE PRELIMINARY REPORT ON THE ILOG-HILABANGAN RIVER BASIN IS IN REPRODUCTION. THE AERO SERVICE CORP CONTINUED THE TOPOGRAPHIC MAP AND MOSAIC WORK UNDER ITS CONTRACT WITH THE US BUREAU OF RECLAMATION. ALL MOSAICS, EXCEPT CAGAYAN NORTH, HAVE BEEN ACCEPTED. INSPECTION AND CORRECTION OF ALL TOPOGRAPHIC RESERVOIR SITE MAPS, EXCEPT PUNCAN MOUNTAIN, ARE IN PROGRESS. THE US BUREAU OF RECLAMATION PROJECT ENGINEER CAME ABOARD 11/30. A PLANNING ENGINEER ARRIVED ON 11/19 FOR 30 DAYS TDY AND COUNTRY CLEARANCE WAS OBTAINED FOR A HYDROLOGIST TO REPORT FOR ASSIGNMENT IN EARLY DECEMBER.

Abstract: This report, one of four regional studies stemming from A.I.D.'s world-wide participant training survey, summarizes the nature and effects of A.I.D. participant training on trainees from five North African countries (Tunisia, Libya, Ethiopia, Morocco, and Spain) between 1951 and 1961.  Included for purpose of comparison are observations about participant training programs in 29 other countries in regard to areas such as program design, pre-departure orientation, English language training, follow-up, and participant satisfaction with training.  (Author abstract, modified)

Abstract: This report is a summary of the effects of A.I.D.'s participant training programs on subsequent utilization of training skills by participants in five Far Eastern countries between 1951 and 1961 (Taiwan, Korea, Philippines, Thailand, and Vietnam).  The study draws on data collected in A.I.D.'s World-wide Participant Training Survey.  No specific recommendations are made but useful insights are provided into the complex issue of measuring the impact of trainng in participants' return-home situation. (Participant training abstract)

Abstract: This report summarizes the findings of 23 country studies of A.I.D.'s participant training program.  The 23 studies were based on standardized written questionnaires, oral interviews, and other methodology in accordance with guidelines provided by AID/W.  The present report, directed primarily toward Agency offiicals and others whose interests or responsibilities in participant training transcend the country level, focuses on the transfer and use of development-related skills acquired by training.  (NOTE:  The final chapter, a review of key findings, is missing.)  (Author abstract, modified)

Abstract: This report is one of a series which provides basic descriptive and evaluative data on the participant training program in each of the four A.I.D. regions.  It provides a synopsis of the nature and long-term effects of A.I.D. participant training programs in eleven Latin American countries spanning the period 1942-61 and covering 3,480 participants. The findings in the study are drawn from the world-wide survey of former A.I.D. participants initiated in 1959 and still in progress in certain countries at the time this report was prepared.  No specific recommendations are included, but the report contains useful insights into the operation and impact of participant training.  (Participant training abstract)

Abstract: Evaluates project performance from 7/1/65 to 6/15/66 in Afghanistan. Project aids Royal Govt of Afghanistan (RGA) to develop financial & administrative techniques to run RGA's cadastral, tax, & administrative programs more efficiently. Evaluator feels contractor has a clear understanding of the scope & nature of contract objectives & has demonstrated good leadership both in Afghanistan & its US office.  Adequate, realistic goals have been developed which assure completion of contract objectives on-schedule. The Ministry of Finance (MOF) has hired more staff & is engaged in training personnel from other RGA agencies.  The new MOF Junior Advisor has designed & installed a new central accounting structure for Kabul University.  MOF on-the-job training visits to various RGA agencies resulted in a 90% completion rate (previously 60%) of daily expenditure reports prepared by RGA agencies.  The lack of a feasible classificatn plan & administrative organization to administer land classification has been eliminated with the completion & RGA's acceptance of the Land Registratn Manual (LRM) & Arable Land Classification Manuals.  These manuals pave the way for a modern cadastral system in Afghanistan.  The LRM defines steps in land registration processes; settlement of land disputes; conveyancing; recording rights & encumbrances of both individuals & RGA; & limitations of land ownership. Under contractor leadership the first Provincial land registration offices will be opened in 1966 in Kandahar, Helmand, & Kabul, with plans to soon open others in Ghanzi & Kunduz.  Offices will be manned by the first cadastral surveyors which have been graduated & given career civil service positions. The Machine Records Division has developed good ledgers & is preparing reports for the Accounting Department; year-end closing & request cash procedures have been designed, improved & installed; Agency Budget officers were trained in the use of the new budget manual; & new income tax laws have been defined in an income tax manual. Evaluator feels RGA will be able to administer program on its own after contract termination.

Abstract: EVALUATES PROJECT PERFORMANCE FROM 7/1/65 TO 11/16/66 IN AFGHANISTAN. PROJ AIDS ROYAL GOVT OF AFGHANISTAN (RGA) DEVEL FINANCIAL & ADMIN TECHNIQUES TO RUN RGA'S CADASTRAL,TAX & ADMIN PROGRAMS. EVALUATOR FEELS CONTRACTOR HAS A CLEAR UNDERSTANDING OF THE SCOPE & NATURE OF CONTRACT OBJECTIVES & HAS DEMONSTRATED GOOD LEADERSHIP BOTH IN AFGHANISTAN & ITS US OFFICE. ADEQUATE,REALISTIC GOALS HAVE BEEN DEVEL WHICH ASSURE COMPLETN OF CONTRACT OBJECTIVES ON-SCHEDULE. CONTRACTOR HAS PERFORMED WELL BY: ADOPTING EFFECTIVE METHODS OF SELECTN,USE INSPECTN & MAINTENANCE OF EQUIPMT; & DEVELOPING HARMONIOUS,SATISFYING WORKING RELATNSHIPS WITH RGA & MISSION STAFFS. COURSES IN LAND REGISTRATN & CLASSISICATN HAVE BEEN ADDED TO THCADASTRAL SURVEY SCHOOL (CSS) WHICH HAS GRADUATED 16 STUDENTS DURING EVALUATN PERIOD & 322 STUDENTS SINCE PROJ'S BEGINNING. TRAINING GOALS FALL SHORT BY 78 STUDENTS DUE TO RECENT LOW REGISTRATNS & DISMISSALS FOR ACADEMIC REASONS. RGA PLANS TO INCREASE ENROLLMT DURING NEXT REGISTRATN PERIOD & TRAIN LOCALS TO FILL POSITNS BEING VACATED BY 4 FILIPINO INSTRUCTO S IN 1967. TOTAL SURVEYING OPERATNS HAVE IMPROVED. THE CADASTRAL SURVEY HAS ESTABLISHED A GEODETIC CONTROL TRAVERSE AROUND KABUL. METHODS HAVE BEEN DEVEL TO PRODUCE QUICK EVALUATNS OF LOW VALUE LAND LEAVING THE DETAILED WORK FOR LATER. KANDAHAR OFFICE,STAFFED BY CSS GRADUATES,WILL OPEN IN NOV. THE MINISTRIES OF REAL ESTATE,JUSTICE & FINANCE HAVE AGREED ON THE PRINCIPLES & FIRST REGISTRATN TEST WHICH IF SUCCESSFUL WILL BE USED IN ALL PROVINCES. UNDER CONTRACTER LEADERSHIP, PREPARATION AND SUBMISSN OF DAILY EXPENDITURES HAVE IMPROVED; THE ACCOUNTING DEPT HAS SUBMITTED ITS FIRST QUARTERLY & SEMIANNUAL FINANCIAL REPORT; THE PCV-SYS DIV TEAM IS NOW FREE TO AUDIT REPORTS & ELIMINATE DIFFICULTIES; PAS HAS DESIGNED FORMS & PROCEDURES TO ASSIST THE TREASURY DEPT IN SELLING & REDEEMING GOVT BONDS; & THE REVENUE ADVISOR POSITN HAS BEEN FILLED WHICH SHOULD ALLOW INCOME TAX LAW IMPLEMENTATN DURING THE NEXT PERIOD. EVALUATOR FEELS ADEQUATE ACTNS ARE BEING MADE TO ENABLE AFGHANISTAN TO ADMINISTER PROJ AFTER CONTRACT TERMINATN.

Abstract: AUDITS PROJECT TO FINANCE THE KOOKDONG MINK COMPANY, LTD. (KMCL) TO ESTABLISH A MINK RANCH IN ORDER TO PROVIDE KOREA WITH A COMMODITY WHICH IS READILY MARKETABLE IN THE FREE WORLD AND WOULD THUS EARN FOREIGN EXCHANGE. THIS AUDIT COVERS THE PERIOD 12/64 TO 6/66 AND IS BASED ON REVIEW OF KMCL'S FINANCIAL RECORDS AND ON-SITE VISITS. THE AUDIT CONCERNS USAID COOLEY LOAN #489-E-025 AND SUB-LOAN #901 GRANTED TO KMCL UNDER USAID DEVELOPMENT LOAN #489-A-007 TO THE KOREAN RECONSTRUCTION BANK (KRB). THE DEVELOPMENT AND FINANCE DIVISION (DFD) AND THE KRB ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR LOAN ADMINISTRATION. THE PROJECT HAS BEEN UNSUCCESSFUL. NO MINK PELTS HAVE BEEN EXPORTED AND A KOREAN CPA AUDIT REPORT DISCLOSED A LOSS OF 2.9 MILLION (EQUIVALENT TO $10,700) FOR THE YEAR ENDING 12/31/65. ONLY 600 OF THE PLANNED 3,750 MINK WERE RETAINED AS BREEDERS. THERE HAVE BEEN NUMEROUS RANCH MANAGEMENT DISPUTES. IT APPEARS DOUBTFUL THAT THIS PROJECT WILL SUCCEED AS A FOREIGN EXCHANGE EARNER FOR KOREA. THIS AUDIT DISCLOSED SEVERAL INSTANCES REQUIRING CORRECTIVE ACTION. LOAN PROCEEDS APPEAR TO HAVE BEEN UTILIZED IN AN UNREASONABLE MANNER. SOME COMMODITIES WERE CONTRACTED FOR PRIOR TO THE ELIGIBILITY DATA STIPULATED IN THE LOAN AGREEMENT AND IT IS DOUBTFUL THAT FULL VALUE HAS BEEN RECEIVED FOR COMMODITIES AND SERVICES PROCURED. SUPPORTIVE DOCUMENTATION IS LACKING FOR EXPENDITURES MADE. KMCL HAS BEEN NEGLIGENT IN PROVIDING GITTLEMAN'S, THE MINK RANCH'S MAJOR OWNER, ITS STOCK CERTIFICATES AS ENTITLED. KMCL HAS INVESTED IN A RABBIT-RAISING PROJECT IN VIOLATION OF THE LOAN AGREEMENT PROVISION WHICH PROHIBITS INVESTMENT IN UNRELATED PROJECTS. KMCL HAS INADEQUATE BUSINESS/PROPERTY INSURANCE COVERAGE. THEREFORE, IF USAID IS TO CONTINUE FUNDING THE PROJECT, IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT DFD OBTAIN FROM KRB DETAILED JUSTIFICATION AND DOCUMENTATION FOR EXPENDITURES MADE; REQUEST THAT KMCL ISSUE STOCK TO GITTLEMAN'S; INFORM KMCL THAT, UNLESS THEY CAN PROVE THAT THE RABBIT-RAISING PROJECT IS RELATED TO THE MINK RANCH, THE RANCH MUST DIVEST ITSELF OF ANY INTEREST IN THE PROJECT; VERIFY THE EXTENT OF INSURANCE COVERAGE AND ASSURE THAT ADEQUATE COVERAGE IS OBTAINED.

Abstract: 9 AUG 1966 USAID AIRGRAM ANALYZES 4/1-6/30/66 QUARTERLY REPORT BY UNIV OF WISCONSIN (UW) CONTRACTOR OF ONGOING UW/USAID/UNIV OF RIO GRANDE DO SOL (URGS) COOP PROJ. OBJECTIVE OF PROJ IS TO DVLP LAND GRANT COLLEGE CONCEPT AT URGS THROUGH INSTITUTIONAL REORGANIZATION AND UPGRADING OF FACULTY,CURRIC & FACILITIES. ONLY 8 OF 13 CONTRACT POSITIONS CURRENTLY FILLED. VACANCIES NOT LIKELY TO BE FILLED UNTIL 1/1/67,POSING REAL PROBLEM OF STAFF OVERLOAD DUE TO INCREASE IN PROJ WORK & CONTINUING PROJS BEGUN BY PREVIOUS STAFF. REPORT JUDGED VERY ENCOURAGING RELATIVE TO ATTAINMENT OF PROJ OBJ. URGS IS BEGINNING TO REACH OUT INTO THE STATE AND BE OF REAL SERVICE TO FARMERS THROUGH ITS RESEARCH,EXTENSION DEMO, & ADULT EDUC ACTIVITIES. STUDIES IN SOIL FERTILITY CROPS & FORAGE HAVE DEMONSTRATED TREMENDOUS INCREASES IN YIELDS FOLLOWING USE OF FERTILIZERS & IMPROVED VARIETIES. PRACTICAL RESEARCH IS UNDERWAY ON CREDIT INFO FLOW TO FARMER USERS & PRODUCTION PROBLEMS CONFRONTING FARMERS. CONTRACT PROJS ACTIVE IN THE DVLP OF GRAD PROGRAMS,TEACHING OF GRAD COURSES,AND ADVISING OF STUDENTS & GUIDANCE OF THEIR THESIS WORK. NUMEROUS EXTENSION & TRNG ACTIVITIES WERE CARRIED OUT; PARTICULARLY ENCOURAGING WAS INCREASING COOPERATION WITH STATE EXTENSION SERVICE. PROJ HAS ALSO ASSISTED NATL VOCATIONAL AGRIC OFFICE IN DEVELOPING VOC AGRIC SCHOOL CURRIC & ADULT FARMER COURSES. PARTIC TRNG HAS DEVELOPED VERY SATISFACTORILY. 23 PARTICIPANTS(13 FOR MS AND 10 FOR PHD PROGRAMS) ARE BEING PREPARED FOR STUDY IN US DURING NEXT 2 FISCAL YEARS. 4 OBSERVATION STUDY TOURS ALSO BEING ARRANGED. MARKED PROGRESS HAS TAKEN PLACE WITH RESPECT TO INSTITUTION BUILDING. THE URGS FACULTY OF AGRONOMY/VETERINARY IS CURRENTLY UNDERGOING REORGANIZATION/RESTRUCTURING WITH PLANS FOR A NEW SOILS DEPARTMENT WITHIN THE FACULTY. SLOW RELEASE OF PROJ'S BRAZILIAN FUNDS CONTINUES TO BE A PROBLEM,BUT URGS IS RAPIDLY GAINING EXPERIENCE IN MEETING THE MULTITUDE OF REGULATIONS CONNECTED WITH DISBURSEMENT OF THESE FUNDS. MISSION COMMENDS UW TEAM FOR EXCELLENT WORK.

Abstract: EVALUATES USAID ASSISTANCE TO THE GOVT OF THE PHILIPPINES FROM 8/1/66-8/31/66 TO UNDERTAKE SURVEYS AND STUDIES PREPARATORY TO THE FORMULATION OF COMPREHENSIVE DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS FOR THE NATION'S SEVEN MAJOR RIVER BASINS. THUS FAR, THE FEASIBILITY REPORT ON THE UPPER PAMPANGA RIVER PROJECT, THE CAGAYAN AND CATABATO BASIN REPORTS ARE IN FINAL REPRODUCTION. DRAFT REPORTS ARE BEING PREPARED FOR THE AUGUSAN, BICOL, ILOG-HILABANGAN BASINS. THE DRAFT OF A PRELIMINARY REPORT ON THE CENTRAL LUZON BASIN WAS DISTRIBUTED 6/10/66. THE AERO SERVICE CORP CONTINUED TOPOGRAPHIC MAP AND MOSAIC WORK UNDER ITS CONTRACT WITH THE US BUREAU OF RECLAMATION.

Abstract: EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE OF A SUB-PROJECT OF THE BRAZILIAN ELEMENTARY EDUCATION PROJECT IN THE STATE OF MARANHAO FOR THE PERIOD 10/22/63 -- 4/30/66. PURPOSE OF SUB-PROJ WAS TO IMPROVE EDUC FACILITIES,TEACHING,AND ADMINISTRATION. INFORMATION FOR THIS EVAL WAS GATHERED THROUGH MEETINGS WITH STATE OFFICIALS,MAYORS,TEACHERS & CITIZENRY,REVIEWS OF ACCOUNTING RECORDS,AND ON-SITE VISITS. ONLY 66 OF 1700 TARGETED NEW CLASSROOMS HAD BEEN CONSTRUCTED AND 50 OF 300 TARGETED EXISTING CLASSRMS HAD BEEN RECONSTRUCTED AT TIME OF THIS EVAL. THESE SHORTFALLS WERE THE RESULT OF SEVERAL FACTORS. THE ENGINEERING STAFF OF THE COMISSAC EXECUTIVE DO PLANO EDUCATIONAL DO MARANHAO (CEPLEMA),THE STATE AGENCY RESPONSIBLE FOR CONSTRCTN,LACKED THE COMPETENACE & PERSONNEL TO ADMINISTER THIS PROJ.CEPLEMA FIELD INSPECTORS,WHO ASSISTED COMMUNITY MAYORS IN CONSTRCTN MATTERS,COULD NOT,IN MANY CASES,RECOGNIZE FAULTY DESIGN OR CONSTRCTN. CEPLEMA DID NOT USE COMPETITIVE BIDDING PROCEDURES FOR CONSTRCTN CONTRACTS AND DID NOT CAREFULLY ADMINISTER CONSTRCTN BUDGETS. THERE WERE SEVERAL INSTANCES OF MISAPPROPIATION OF FUNDS BY CONTRACTORS,FIELD INSPECTORS & MAYORS. CEPLEMA APPARENTLY UNDERSTOOD RECONSRUCTN TO MEAN NORMAL MAINTENANCE WITH THE RESULT THAT VERY LITTLE SUBSTANTIVE RECONSTRCTN WAS UNDERTAKEN. FINALLY,STATE CONSTRCTN CONTRACTORS WERE FOUND TO BE INADEQUATE. MANY OF THE SCHOOLS WHICH WERE CONSTRCTD/RECONSTRCTD WERE BEING UNDERUTILIZED. SEVERAL WERE LOCATED IN EITHER VERY SPARSELY-POPULATED AREAS OR AREAS WHICH WERE ADEQUATELY SERVED BY EXISTING SCHOOLS. A SUFFICIENT NO OF TEACHERS COULD NOT BE FOUND TO ENABLE THE FULL OPERATN OR EVEN OPENING OF OTHER PROJ SCHLS. THERE WAS NO GENERAL MAINT PROG FOR PROJ SCHLS, THUS,MANY WERE DETERIORATING RAPIDLY. THE PROJ'S ADULT LITERACY PROGRAM WAS CANCELLED BY THE GOB MIN OF EDUC AND BOTH SUDENE(LOAN RECIPIENT & ADMINISTRATOR) & USAID/B/NEAO EDUC BRANCH WERE SLOW TO FORMULATE REPLACEMENT PROGS. ONLY 97 OF 1000 TARGETED TEACHERS RECIEVE TRNG UNDER THE PROJ'S EMERGENCY TEACHER TRNG PROJ--A MAJOR REASON FOR SCHL STAFFING PROBLEMS. CEPLEMA'S POOR MGMT CAPABILITY ALLOWED ONLY 2/3 OF AMTS PLEDGED BY USAID TO BE UTILIZED

Abstract: EVALUATES USAID ASSISTANCE TO THE GOVT OF THE PHILIPPINES FROM 7/1/66-7/31/66 TO UNDERTAKE SURVEYS AND STUDIES PREPARATORY TO THE FORMULATION OF COMPREHENSIVE DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS FOR THE NATION'S SEVEN MAJOR RIVER BASINS. A DOCUMENT OUTLINING BASIC PRINCIPLES AND PROCEDURES RECOMMENDED BY THE US BUREAU OF RECLAMATION TEAM FOR CONDUCTING WATER RESOURCES SURVEYS WAS TRANSMITTED TO THE GOP BUREAU OF PUBLIC WORKS ON 7/7/66. THE CAGAYAN AND COTABATO BASIN REPORTS ARE IN FINAL REPRODUCTION AND DRAFT REPORTS ON AGUSAN, BICOL AND ILOG-HILABANGAN ARE UNDERWAY. THE FEASIBILITY REPORT ON THE UPPER PAMPANGA RIVER WILL BE READY FOR FINAL REPRODUCTION 8/10/66. THE DRAFT OF A PRELIMINARY REPORT ON THE CENTRAL LUZON BASIN HASBEEN DISTRIBUTED.

Abstract: PROJECT IS IN RESPONSE TO NATIONAL HIGHWAY DEPARTMENT REQUEST TO AID IT IN TRANSFORMING ITSELF FROM FEDERAL HIGHWAY OPERATING AGENCY INTO HIGHWAY PLANNING, CONTROL AND STANDARD-SETTING ORGANIZATION. TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE IS AVAILABLE FROM US BUREAU OF PUBLIC ROADS, RATHER THAN FROM PRIVATE CONSULTING FIRMS. PROJECT ALSO CONSISTS OF HIGHWAY MAINTENANCE EQUIPMENT AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE PROGRAM IN STATE OF SAO PAULO. LEVEL OF MAINTENANCE PROVIDED EQUALS NEEDS FOR MAINTAINING EXISTING ROAD NETWORK PLUS ROADS TO BE ADDED TO SYSTEM OVER NTXT 3 YEARS. CONSULTING ENGINEERS ARE EMPLOYED TO ADVISE AND ASSIST STATE IN PLANNING AND IMPLEMENTING MAINTENANCE PROGRAMS INCLUDING USE OF REORGANIZATION RECOMMENDATIONS.

Abstract: APPROXIMATELY $6MILLION WILL BE EARMARKED FOR SIPA'S (SERVICIO DE INVESTIGACION Y PROMOCION AGRARIA) COASTAL PROGRAM OF SUPERVISED CREDIT. APPROXIMATELY $2.25 MILLION OF THE LOAN WILL BE FOR THE AGRARIAN REFORM PROGRAM IN LA CONVENCION AND SIERRA CENTRAL ZONES, ONRA (OFICINA NACIONAL DE REFORMA AGRARIA) EXECUTES THIS PROGRAM. THE FUNDS LENT WILL BE USED EXCLUSIVELY FOR CREDITS WITH THE EXCEPTION OF $250000 FOR TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE. TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE WILL BE PROVIDED TO TRAIN PERUVIAN COUNTERPARTS IN THE TECHNIQUES OF EVALUATION AND TO ADVISE ONRA AND SIPA IN ADMINISTRATIVE ASPECTS OF THE PROGRAM INCLUDING ADVICE ON LOAN PROCEDURES.

Abstract: LOAN TO GOE PERMITS INTENSIFIED MALARIA ERADICATION PROGRAM. EXECUTION IS RESPONSIBILITY OF NATL MALARIA ERADICATION SERVICE(SNEM), WHICH WAS JOINTLY ADMINISTERED BY USAID & MINISTRY OF HEALTH(MOH), BUT IS NOW INTEGRAL PART OF MOH. AID FUNDS SUPPORT ATTACK PHASE: INTENSIVE HOUSE SPRAYING WITH DDT EVERY = MO AND FEVER DETECTION PROGRAM. SNEM VOLUNTEERS TAKE BLOOD SAMPLES, GIVE ANTI-MALARIA DRUGS TO PERSONS SUFFERING FROM HIGH FEVER. IF TEST INDICATES MALARIA, VOLUNTEER PERFORMS INTENSIVE CASE STUDY: TREATING VICTIM, SPRAYING HOUSES, TAKING BLOOD SAMPLES FROM THOSE IN CONTACT WITH VICTIM. OPERATIONAL AND FINANCIAL PROBLEMS LED TO DELAY (LOAN GRANTED IN 1966, PROJECT UNFINISHED IN 1971). UNICEF, PAHO CONTRIBUTE.

Abstract: THE WORK REPORTED HERE WAS CONDUCTED IN CARACAS FROM 1963 THROUGH 1966 BY THE SIMULMATICS CORPORATION, WORKING IN COLLABORATION WITH THE UNIVERSIDAD CENTRAL DE VENEZUELA AND CORDIPLAN, THE VENEZUELAN GOVERNMENT PLANNING AGENCY. A SERIES OF MODELS OF THE VENEZUELAN ECONOMY WAS FORMULATED FOR USE IN STUDYING THE NATION'S DEVELOPMENT STRATEGY BY MEANS OF COMPUTER SIMULATION. WITH THIS TECHNIQUE, ALTERNATIVES CAN BE COMPARED IN A WAY THAT OFFERS GUIDANCE TO POLICYMAKERS WITHOUT IMPEDING THEIR USE OF JUDGMENT AND INTUITION IN MAKING PLANNING DECISIONS. THE PRINCIPLES OF SIMULATION ARE BRIEFLY PRESENTED AND THEN ILLUSTRATED BY A DETAILED PLAN FOR A POLICY STUDY. THE ANALYSIS AND EXPERIMENTS TO BE CONDUCTED ARE EXPLAINED. THE STUDY PLAN IS NOT JUST A HYPOTHETICAL ILLUSTRATION; IT IS BASED ON THE ACTUAL SITUATION IN VENEZUELA AND THE CAPABILITIES OF THE MODEL (V-2A) DEVELOPED FOR USE IN SUCH STUDIES. THE AUTHORS RECOMMEND THAT CORDIPLAN CARRY OUT THIS PLAN. FURTHER SECTIONS OF THE REPORT REVIEW THE DEVELOPMENT OF VARIOUS SIMULATION MODELS CONSIDERED, AND EXPLAIN THEIR DIFFERENCES; SUMMARIZE PROBLEMS ENCOUNTERED AND THE WORK DONE IN ANALYZING STATISTICS; DESCRIBE USES TO WHICH THE MODEL V-2 WAS PUT IN HELPING CORDIPLAN IN ITS ECONOMIC PLANNING ACTIVITIES; PRESENT DETAILS OF THE ABSTRACT MODEL; AND PRESENT RECOMMENDATIONS FOR FUTURE ACTIVITIES IN VENEZUELA.

Abstract: COMMUNICABLE DISEASE CENTER ADMINISTERED PROGRAM WHICH ERADICATED SMALLPOX, CURTAILED MEASLES IN 20 WEST AND CENTRAL AFRICAN STATES. SMALLPOX PROGRAM IMPLEMENTED IN 4 STAGES: LOCATION OF OUTBREAK, INVESTIGATION OF REPORTED CASES, OUTBREAK CONTROL BY VACCINATION OF AREA, COMMUNICATION AMONG CONCERNED NATIONS. LAST CASE REPORTED IN 5/70; SURVIELLANCE CONTINUED UNTIL 12/72. LOGISTICS PROBLEMS (PRESERVATION OF VACCINE) MADE MEASLES CONTROL MORE DIFFICULT. PROGRAM ACHIEVED VARYING DEGREES OF SUCCESS BY VACCINATING 6-MO- TO 4-YR-OLD CHILDREN DURING SMALLPOX CAMPAIGN. REGIONAL OFFICE IN LAGOS COORDINATED EFFORTS OF NATIONS, REGIONAL ORGANIZATIONS, CDC. TRAINING, EXPERIENCE, EQUIPMENT UPGRADED NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICES.

Abstract: After Independence in 1947, India adopted, as its first goal, improvement of the living standard of its now more than 470 million people.  Since then, the Indian Government has been engaged in a massive effort of planned economic development on democratic lines.  The country has completed three five year plans with progressively larger plan outlays in each successive plan.  These fifteen years of planned development efforts have resulted in significant addition to national and per capita incomes.  A large number of friendly nations have assisted India in her development efforts.  The United States contribution during this period has been and continues to remain massive.  The basic purpose of U.S. assistance is to help India become economically self-sufficient on all fronts.  Accordingly, the United States has played a significant role in the development of economic and social infra-structure, in transportation (railways, roads and air), irrigation and power,  education, health, etc., and has also assisted in agricultural and industrial fields by providing project and non-project assistance.  The forms of aid have changed with the changing needs of India, as well as changes in methods of administration of U.S. foreign aid programs.  This report attempts to provide the magnitude, mechanics and results of United States assistance to India in helping her achieve a self-sustaining growth as rapidly as possible.  (Author abstract)

Abstract: SATISFACTORY PROGRESS IN IMPLEMENTING PROJECT OUTPUTS AS OF 6/14/66. WATER PRESSURE AND DISCHARGE DATA AND QUENTITATIVE HYDROLOGY DATA ARE MEDIOCRE. EGYPTIAN GENERAL DESERT DEVELOPMENT ORGANIZATION (EGDDO) PERFORMANCE HANDICAPPED BY LACK OF EXPERIENCE IN COMPREHENSIVE GROUNDWATER EVALUATION. EGDDO WAS RESPONSIBLE FOR BOTH STUDY AND PRODUCTION; MAJOR PROBLEM OF PROJECT WAS RAPID CONVERSION OF TEST WELLS TO PRODUCTION, WITHOUT WAITING UNTIL HYDROLOGICAL STUDIES OF WELLS WERE COMPLETED. TEST WELLS HAD SUFFICIENT DISCHARGE FOR IRRIGATION. CONVERSION RESULTED IN MEDIOCRE QUANTITATIVE DATA WHICH SLOWED PROJECT AND CAUSED REDUCTION IN SCOPE TO INCLUDE ONLY KHARGA AND DAKHLA OASES. FULL-TIME QUANTITATIVE HYDROLOGIST MIGHT HAVE OVERCOME CONVERSION OF TEST WELLS TO PRODUCTION. GUIDANCE OF PROJECT WAS SERIOUSLY DISRUPTED FROM 8/64-3/65 BECAUSE THERE WAS NO CHIEF ADVISOR.

Abstract: AID LOAN OF $1,500,000 ASSIST IN FINANCING ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS IN WEST AFRICA. FUNDS ARE MADE AVAILABLE THROUGH SUB-LOANS ADMINISTERED BY DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION (WEST AFRICA))DCWA), WHOLLY-OWNED SUBSIDIARY OF COMMONWEALTH DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION, GUARANTOR OR LOAN. PROJECTS WILL INCLUDE PRIVATE OR MIXED PUBLIC-PRIVATE ENTERPRISES CONTROLLED BY PRIVATE INTERESTS IN AGRICULTURE, FORESTRY, MINING, MANUFACTURING, TRANSPORTATION, HOTELS, ETC. PROJECTS INVOLVING PUBLIC STATUTORY CORPORATIONS IN WATER, ELECTRICITY, PORT DEVELOPMENT ARE POSSIBLE IF ENTERPRISES ARE RUN ALONG COMMERCIAL LINES. BORROWERS IN NIGERIA, GHANA, SIERRA LEONE, GAMBIA SUBMIT SPECIFIC LIST OF ELIGIBLE ENTERPRISES TO AID FOR APPROVAL.

Abstract: TECHNICAL AND FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, AND TEACHER TRAINING WILL ASSIST EL SALVADOR'S MINISTRY OF EDUCATION(MOE) TO REFORM ITS EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS WITH MODERN SUBJECTS, A LEARNER-ORIENTED APPROACH, IMPROVED TEACHING, EDUCATIONAL TECHNOLOGY, AND EXTENSION OF BASIC EDUCATION FOR PRIMARY AND SECONDARY SCHOOL STUDENTS. INSTITUTIONAL TV(ITV) IS THE BASIC COMPONENT OF THE PROJECT, AROUND WHICH CLASSROOM CONSTRUCTION AND TEACHER TRAINING, AS WELL AS THE IMPROVEMENT OF MOE ADMINISTRATIVE CAPABILITIES WILL BE DESIGNED. AFTER INSTRUCTIONAL MATERIALS EXPERTS TRAIN COUNTERPARTS AND TEACHERS, AND PREPARE TV LESSONS, ITV WILL BE BROADCAST TO GRADES SEVEN, EIGHT, AND NINE (PLAN BASICO). A $1.9 MILLION USAID LOAN IS PLANNED IN 1970 TO COMPLETE PLAN BASICO COVERAGE BY THE END OF 1972 WITH RECEIVERS AND TRANSMISSION EQUIPMENT AT NEW,AND TO BE COMPLETED,ITV STUDIOS. ANOTHER $1.2 MILLION LOAN IS EARMARKED TO EXPAND ITV COVERAGE TO PRIMARY SCHOOLS AFTER 1972. STANFORD UNIVERSITY'S ACADEMY FOR EDUCATIONAL DEVELOPMENT(AED) WILL EVAL YEARLY ITV IMPACT, LEARNING GAINS, TEACHER ACCEPTANCE, AND COST-EFFECTIVENESS. AT THE PREVIOUSLY AID-FUNDED NATIONAL NORMAL SCHOOL, ABOUT 1000 PALN BASICO TEACHERS WILL BE RETRAINED IN MODERN METHODS OF INSTRUCTION FOR ONE YEAR. PROGRAMS OF PRE-SERVICE TEACHER EDUCATION AT THE PRIMARY LEVEL,AND IN-SERVICE TRAINING IN REVISED PRIMARY CURRICULUM METHODOLOGY AND UTILIZATION OF ITV FOR APPROXIMATELY 14,000 TEACHERS,WILL BE PROVIDED DURING AFTER-SCHOOL HOURS. CURRICULUM REVISION AND MODERNIZATION WILL BE COMPLETED BY 1970 FOR GRADES ONE THROUGH NINE. CORE SUBJECTS WILL INCLUDE MATH, SCIENCE, SOCIAL STUDIES, LANGUAGE ARTS, AND ENGLISH. THE REFORM OF MOE ADMINISTRATIVE CAPABILITIES WILL BE ACCELERATED WITH THE ASSISTANCE OF CLAPP AND MAYNE, MANAGEMENT CONSULTANTS, WHO WILL WORK WITH MOE COUNTERPARTS IN DESIGNING AND CARRYING-OUT COST-EFFECTIVENESS/BENEFIT AND MANPOWER STUDIES. A DEPARTMENT OF EVALUATION WILL DEVELOP AN IN-CLASS STUDENT EVALUATION SYSTEM WHICH WILL INCLUDE STANDARDIZED TESTS.

Abstract: LOAN TO THE GOVERNMENT OF GUYANA WILL FINANCE US DOLLAR COSTS OF EQIUIPMENT, MATERIAL, AND SERVICES REQUIRED TO CONDUCT FEASIBILITY STUDIES AND PRE-FEASIBILITY STUDIES. THESE STUDIES WILL FOCUS ON VARIOUS ACTIVITIES TO INCREASE ACCESS TO AND DEVELOPMENT OF INLAND GUYANA, WITH EMPHASIS ON THE AGRICULTRAL SECTORS. GOG TENTATIVE LIST OF PROJECTS TO BE FINANCED INCLUDES THE FOLLOWING: A) PRE-FEASIBILITY STUDY OF THE INLAND ROAD WILL DEVELOP MOST FEASIBLE AND ECONOMICAL ROUTE TO LINK COAST WITH RUPUNUNI AREA, NOW ACCESSIBLE ONLY BY AIR; WILL ALSO CONSIDER LINKAGES TO PAN AMERICAN HIGHWAY. B) FEASIBILITY STUDY OF FIRST SEGMENT OF INTERIOR ROAD WILL COVER INITIAL 80 MILES OF ROUTE DETERMINED IN PRE-FEASIBILITY STUDY. C) REVIEW OF TIBOKU HYDROELECTRIC DEVELOPMENT WILL EXAMINE IN DETAIL WORK ALREADY ACCOMPLISHED AND INDICATE ANY GAPS OR SHORTCOMINGS IN ORIGINAL STUDY. D) FEASIBILITY OF A CHANNEL CONNECTING THE MORUKA AND PARAMANI RIVERS TO EXTEND STEAMER TRAFFIC WILL BE STUDIED. E) STUDY OF AGRICULTURAL AND OTHER ECONOMIC POTENTIAL OF MATTHEWS RIDGE AREA, ARAKAKA, AND KAITUMA FOLLOWING CLOSING OF MANGANESE MINES WILL BE UNDERTAKEN; WILL INCLUDE IDENTIFICATION OF AREAS SUITABLE FOR CULTIVATION, RECOMMENDATIONS FOR CROPPING AND LIVESTOCK, STUDY OF FOREST AND MINERAL RESOURCES, AND STUDY OF TOURISM POTENTIAL. F) DEVELOPMENT STUDY FOR THE NORTH WEST DISTRICT WILL IDENTIFY AGRICULTURAL LAND AND RECOMMEND LIVESTOCK AND CROPS; STUDY AND MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS ON FORESTRY AND MINERAL RESOURCES; AND OUTLINE TRANSPORTATION AND CAPITAL REQUIREMENTS FOR THE REGION. G) STUDIES OF NEW AMSTERDAM APPROACHES, WISMAR-ROCKSTONE ROAD, AND ESSEQUIBO ROADS ARE PROPOSED, AS ARE STUDIES OF MACKENZIE-ITUNI-KWAKWANI ROADS. H) AGRICULTURAL SECTOR STUDY WILL IDENTIFY BOTTLENECKS IN PRODUCTION AND DISTRIBUTION PROCESS.

Abstract: LOAN TO THE GOV'T OF URUGUAY (GOU) TO IMPROVE THE NAVIGATIONAL, METEOROLOGICAL, COMMUNICATIONS & INCIDENTAL EQUIPMENT ESSENTIAL TO UPGRADING THE CARRASCO INTERNAT'L AIRPORT (CIA), MONTEVIDEO, TO INTERNAT'L STANDARDS OF SAFETY & OPERATIONS. THE AIR NAVIGATIONAL AIDS TO BE INSTALLED INCLUDE VHF OMNIDIRECTN'L RANGE TRANSMITTER,NON-DIRECTN'L BEACON,HIGH INTENSITY LIGHTING SYS,MEDIUM INTENSITY TAXIWAY LIGHTING SYS,STANDBY POWER GENERATOR,AIRFIELD MARKING EQUIP,VHF TRANSMITTERS-RECEIVERS,MULTI-CHANNEL VOICE RECORDING UNIT,CONTROL TOWER EQUIP,MOBIL RADIO TRANSMITTERS-RECEIVERS,FIXED TELECOMMUNICATNS NETWORK,VEHICLES,RUNWAY END IDENT LIGHT SYS,VISUAL APPROACH SLOPE INFO SYS,INSTRUMT LANDING SYS,CEILING LIGHT PROJECTOR. TRAINING IN OPERATION,MAINTENANCE,REPAIR & INSPECTN OF ALL NAVIGATIONAL & COMMUNICATN AIDS,EQUIPMT & SYSTEMS WILL BE PROVIDED FOR URUGUAYANS. OTHER PROJ ACTIVITIES INCLUSE A 300 METER EXTENSION & 50 METER STOPWAY AS WELL AS STRENGTHENING OF TAXIWAYS & REHABILITATN OF APRON PAVEMENT OF THE CIA'S RUNWAYS. AN ADDITION WILL CONSTRUCTED TO THE TERMINAL BLDG & A UTILITY TUNNEL BUILT TO FACILITATE TRAFFIC FLOW BETWEEN AIRPORT INSTALLATIONS. TO SUPPORT AIRPORT OPERATIONS,MAINTENANCE & REPAIR,THE NATIONAL AIRPORTS COMMISSION(NAC) WILL,IN THE FUTURE,RETAIN ALL REVENUES FROM AIRPORT OPERATIONS. ADDITIONALLY,A NEW USERS RATE SCHEDULE WILL BE PUT INTO EFFECT WHICH WILL INCREASE THE LEVEL OF FEES PRESENTLY CHARGED,DOUBLING THE FIRST YEAR & TRIPLING THE SECOND YEAR FOLLOWING COMPLETION OF CONSTRUCTION & INSTALLATION OF EQUIPMENT. ALTHOUGH THE BANCO DE LA REPUBLICA ORIENTAL DEL URUGUAY IS THE BORROWING AGENCY,THE PROJECT WILL BE IMPLEMENTED & ADMINISTERED BY THE NAC. THE NAC,IN ADDITION TO ADMINISTRATION,WILL PREPARE AN ACCOUNTING SYSTEM PLAN WITH SUFFICIENTLY DETAILED INFORMATION OF CIA COSTS & OPERATIONS TO ENABLE DETERMINATION OF FUTURE BUDGET REQUIREMENTS,DEBT AMORTIZATION & CIA IMPROVEMENTS. PRIMARY PROJECT BENEFICIARY WILL BE THE GOVERNMENT OF URUGUAY,IN THE FORM OF INCREASED REVENUES & STIMULATION OF NATIONAL,REGIONAL & INTERNATIONAL COMMERCE AS CIA IMPROVEMENTS ARE ACCOMPLISHED.

Abstract: EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE OF THE BRAZILIAN ELEM BASIC EDUC PROJECT AS IMPLEMENTED IN THE STATE OF SERGIPE DURING THE PERIOD 7/30/63-5/31/66. PURPOSE OF PROJ WAS TO UPGRADE SCHOOL FACILITIES AND TEACHING & SCHL SUPERVISORY PROGRAMS. EVAL WAS CONDUCTED BY EXAMINING THE RECORDS OF USAID/B AND THE COMISSAO EXECUTIVA PARA PROGRAMAS COOPERATIVOS DE EDUCACAO NO STADO DE SERGIPE (CEPCES) -- THE STATE AGENCY ADMINISTERING THIS PROJ; BY INTERVIEWING STATE OFFICIALS, AND BY MAKING ON-SITE VISITS. ONLY 164 OF THE TARGETED 900 CLASSROOMS WERE CONSTRUCTED OR RECONSTRCTD DURING EVAL PERIOD. APPROX 62% OF THE FUNDS BUDGETED FOR CONST/RECONST WORK WAS EXPENDED WITH ONLY 19% OF THE PHYSICAL GOALS BEING ATTAINED. IT WILL TAKE THE REMAINDER OF THE PROJ FUNDS TO FINISH AN ADDIT 20 SCHLS WHICH ARE IN VARIOUS STAGES OF CONSTRCTN. SEVERAL FACTORS CONTRIBUTED TO THESE SHORTFALLS. CEPCES'S ENGINEERING STAFF LACKED THE COMPETENCE & PERSONNEL TO UNDERTAKE A PROJ OF THIS SIZE. ARCHITECTURAL PLANS WERE USUALLY FAULTY AND COSTLY CORRECTIONS HAD TO BE MADE AFTER CONSTRCTN HAD STARTED. CONSTRCTN CONTRACTOR CAPABILITIES WERE POOR AND COMPLETED BLDGS WERE OFTEN UNSAFE. ALTHOUGH CONSTRCTN CONTRACTS WERE LET TO THE LOWEST BIDDER,CONTRACTS WERE SUBJECT TO UPWARD READJUSTMENTS WHICH INCREASED ORIGINAL BID COSTS BY OVER 50%. ADVSRS FROM LEO A DALY,PROJ ENGINEERING CONSULTANT,WERE NOT PERMITTED TO REVIEW EITHER THE ORIGINAL CONTRACTS OR THE READJSTMNTS. DIFFICULTIES WITH SELECTING & APPROVING SITES RESULTED IN LONG DELAYS. AN END-USE CHECK OF 33 OF THE 5O COMPLETED SCHLS DISCLOSED THAT 6 WERE NOT BEING USED DUE TO FAULTY CONSTRCTN AND 2 WERE CLOSED FOR LACK OF TEACHERS. AS THERE WAS NO SCHL MAINTENANCE PROGRAM,SERIOUS DETERIORATION WAS ALREADY OCCURING IN SOME OF THE SCHLS. THE EMERGENCY TCHR TRNG COMPONENT HAD NOT BEEN INITIATED DUE TO INSUFF TRNG FACILS AND THE ADULT LITERACY PROG WAS CANCELLED BY FEDERAL DECREE AFTER MAR 1964 REVOLUTION. 743 LAY TCHRS(1000 TARGETED) & 28 SUPRVSRS(35 TARG)RECEIVED TRNG. CEPCES ACCOUNTING & REPORTING ACTIVITIES WERE INADEQUATE. MONEY PAID IN ADVANCE FOR EQPMNT PROCUREMENT HAD BEEN INVESTED UNITL PROCRMNTS COULD BE MADE.
Ancilary Data: Evaluation period: 30 Jul 1963-31 May 1966

Abstract: EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE OF A SUB-PROJECT OF THE BRAZILIAN ELEMENTARY EDUCATION PROJECT AS IMPLEMENTED IN THE STATE OF CEARA FOR THE PERIOD 6/5/63 THROUGH 4/30/66. PURPOSE OF SUB-PROJ WAS TO UPGRADE THE TEACHING PROGRAM & FACILITIES OF PRIMARY SCHOOLS. INFORMATION FOR THIS EVAL WAS DEVELOPED THROUGH EXAMINATIONS OF USAID/B/NEAO RECORDS,DISCUSSIONS WITH GOB,STATE & CITY OFFICIALS,AND FIELD TRIPS TO 60 SELECTED SCHOOLS. OF THE 2200 CLASSROOMS PLANNED FOR CONSTRUCTION,WORK WAS COMPLETED ON ONLY 14. ALTHOUGH ONLY 200 CLSSRMS WERE SCHEDULED FOR RECONSTRUCTION,THE STATE REPORTED THAT 1951 HAD BEEN RENOVATED. THIS CLAIM APPEARED TO BE HIGHLY SUSPECT. FOR EXAMPLE.100 SCHLS WHICH WAS REPORTED AS RECONSTRUCTED WERE INSEAD FOUND TO BE ABANDONED. SEVERAL FACTORS CONTRIBUTED TO CONSTRCTN SHORTFALLS. HEAVY INFLATION IN THE BRAZILIAN CONSTRCTN INDUSTRY COUPLED WITH THE STATE'S DISBURSMENT OF LESS THAN 1/3 OF THE MONEYS IT HAD PLEDGED DRASTICALLY REDUCED THE AMT OF CONSTRUCTN THAT COULD BE FUNDED. THE ENGINEERING STAFFOF THE COMISSAO EXECUTIVA DE PROGRAMS ESPECIAIS  (CEPE), THE ADMINSTRATOR OF THE CONSTRUCTN,APPEARED UNABLE TO OPERATE A PROGRAM OF THIS MAGNITUDE. CONSTRCTN PLANNING WAS UNSATISFACTORY AND MUCH OF THE ACTUAL CONSTRCTN WAS OF POOR QUALITY. A CONTINUOUS MAINTENANCE PROG FOR STATE SCHOOLS DID NOT EXIST; THOSE NEW FACILITIES WHICH WERE OPERATIONAL WERE DETERIORATING UNCHECKED. TRAINING TARGETS WERE ALSO NOT MET. AS LESS THAN 1/4 OF THE AMT PLANNED WAS ACTUALLY EXPENDED,ONLY 1/3 OF THE TOTAL NO OF TEACHERS & SUPERVISORS ANTICIPATED RECEIVED TRNG. THE ADULT LITERACY PROG WAS CANCELLED BY THE MOE SUBSEQUENT TO THE MARCH 1964 REVOLUTION. FINALLY,THERE WAS A LACK OF SOUND BUDGETARY CONTROL WHICH MAY HAVE RESULTED IN MISAPPROPRIATION OF FUNDS. IT IS RECOMMENDED: 1)THE CEPE SHOULD SUBMIT CONSTRCTN & SITE PLANS PRIOR TO FUND REQUESTS AND SHOULD COMPLETE BACKLOG OF APPROVED CONSTRCTN BEFORE REQUESTING FUNDS FOR ADDIT CONSTRCTN; 2)CEPE SHOULD RECTIFY ITS BIDDING & CONTRACT PROCEDURES; 3)SUDENE SHOULD VERIFY ALL RECONSTRCTN INVOICES; 4)LEO A DALY CO,AID CONSULTANT,SHOULD APPROVE ENGINEERING SPECS AND REHAB OF ALL SCHOOLS.
Ancilary Data: Evaluation period: 5 Jun 1963-30 Apr 1966

Abstract: EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE OF THE BRAZILIAN ELEM & BASIC EDUC PROJECT AS IMPLEMENTED IN THE STATE OF PARAIBA FOR THE PERIOD 7/27/63-5/31/66. PURPOSE OF PROJ WAS TO UPGRADE SCHOOL FACILITIES AND THE TEACHING & SUPERVISORY PROGRAMS. INFORMATION FOR THIS EVAL WAS COLLECTED THRU DISCUSSIONS THE SECRETARY OF EDUC & OFFICIALS OF SETOR DO CONVENIO INTERAMERICANO (SECI) -- THE STATE AGENCY RESPONSIBLE FOR IMPLEMENTING PROJ'S CONSTRUCTION ACTIVITES, REVIEWS OF PERTINENT RECORDS,MEETINGS WITH TEACHERS,AND ON-SITE OBSERVATIONS. WORK HAD NOT BEEN UNDERTAKEN ON ANY OF THE 1250 CLASSROOMS TARGETED FOR CONSTRUCTION AT TIME OF EVAL. RECONSTRCTN WAS EXECUTED ON ONLY 236 OF THE PLANNED 900 CLSSRMS. THREE TEACHER TRNG CENTERS WERE COMPLETED AT A COST OF CR $210 MILLION VS A BUDGETED COST OF CR $60 MIL. THESE SHORTFALLS CAN BE TRACED TO SEVERAL FACTORS. SECI ENGINEERING STAFF WAS DEFICIENT IN NUMBERS & EXPERTISE. PROPER PLANS & SPECS WERE NOT DEVELOPED FOR RECONSTRCTN WORK. OPEN BIDDING CONTRACT PROCEDURES WERE NOT CONDUCTED,AND CONSTRCTN WORK WAS NOT CLOSELY MONITORED. RECONSTRCTN DID NOT FOLLOW A PREDETERMINED PLAN AND WAS NOT UNDER STRICT BUDGETARY CONTROL. THERE WERE CASES OF OVERCHARGING BY CONTRACTORS AND MISAPPROPRIATION OF FUNDING BY SECI UNITS. SUBSTANDARD MATRLS WERE USED INSTEAD OF KILN,BRICK,CEMENT,OR CONCRETE,RESULTING IN INFERIOR & DANGEROUS CONSTRCTN. THE FACILITIES RECONSTRCTED WERE OPERATIVE BUT THE LACK OF A STATE MAINTENANCE PROG FOR SCHLS IS EXPECTED TO RESLUT IN THE RAPID DETERIORATION OF THESE FACILS. CONSIDERABLY LESS FUNDING WAS SPENT ON TRNG THAN ANTICIPATED,LEADING TO FAILURE IN ACHIEVING TARGETS. SOME FUNDS WERE DIVERTED TO TRNG PROGS NOT ORIGINALLY PLANNED SUCH AS THOSE RELATING TO SUPERVISORY TRNG & ADULT LITERACY. NO PROJ FUNDS WERE SPENT ON LAY TCHR TRNG AS PLANNED; THE STATE,HOWEVER,HAS SPENT ITS OWN MONEY FOR THIS PURPOSE AND 645 TCHRS RECIEVED TRNG. AT TIME OF EVAL,THE STATE OF PARAIBA WAS 22 MOS BEHIND IN ITS AGREED COUNTERPART PAYMENTS. ALSO,QUESTIONABLE SECI FINANCIAL PRACTICES CAUSED SUDENE(GOB'S ADMINSTRATOR OF THIS LOAN) TO BLOCK FURTHUR DISBURSEMENTS UNTIL THESE PRACTICES COULD BE CORRECTED.

Abstract: EVALUATES, FROM 3/26/64 TO 9/12/66, PERFORMANCE OF A UNIVERSITY OF WISCONSIN CONTRACT TEAM IN A PROJECT TO CONDUCT RESEARCH ON THE PROBABLE BENEFITS OF INCREASED ECONOMIC COOPERATION AMONG ASIAN COUNTRIES AND THE CONDITIONS REQUIRED TO REALIZE THESE BENEFITS. EVALUATION IS BASED ON AN AID REVIEW. PROJECT CONSISTS OF COMPARATIVE ANALYSES OF THE ECONOMIC PLANS OF ASIAN COUNTRIES AND CASE STUDIES OF REGIONAL AND NATIONAL INSTITUTIONS. PRIORITY IS BEING GIVEN TO REGIONAL TRADE PATTERNS AND MOVEMENTS OF CAPITAL AND LABOR WITHIN AND EXTERNAL TO THE REGION. ALSO BEING STUDIED ARE POSSIBLE BARRIERS TO INTERNATIONAL TRADE, EG, TARIFFS, GOVERNMENT REGULATIONS, AND DIFFERENCES IN NATIONAL DEVELOPMENT PLANS WITHIN THE REGION. IN THE FUTURE, ATTEMPTS TO INCREASE PRODUCTION IN AGRICULTURE AND MANUFACTURING WILL BE ANALYZED IN RELATION TO ACTUAL AND POTENTIAL TRADE FLOWS. IN LIGHT OF THIS ANALYSIS, THE FEASIBILITY OF SELECTED REGIONAL PROJECTS, INCLUDING THOSE RELATIVE TO INCREASED US DEVELOPMENT EFFORTS IN THE AREA, WILL BE STUDIED. CONTRACTOR HAS SUBMITTED FOR AID REVIEW 9 FINAL AND OTHER DRAFT REPORTS. A PRELIMINARY REPORT HAS BEEN MADE ON A REGIONAL PAYMENT UNION,AND A CONFERENCE FOR A DISCUSSION OF THE PROJECT BY ASIAN AND OTHER SCHOLARS HAS BEEN ARRANGED IN BANGKOK EARLY IN 1967. CONTRACTOR HAS ALREADY ENLISTED SERVICES OF A NUMBER OF ASIAN SCHOLARS AND MAY BECOME A CENTER/CLEARINGHOUSE FOR ASIAN RESEARCH BY ASIAN AND AMERICAN SCHOLARS. CONTRACTOR'S PERFORMANCE IS ADEQUATE, BUT CAPABLE OF IMPROVEMENT, ESPECIALLY IN THE AREAS OF: (1) CLOSER COUPLING OF RESEARCH WITH AID'S PRACTICAL NEEDS IN THE AREA; (2) CLEARER RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN INDIVIDUAL STUDIES AND THE OVERALL WORK PLAN; AND (3) CLOSER SUPERVISION OF JUNIOR RESEARCHERS BY PROJECT DIRECTOR, INCLUDING MAKING MORE SENIOR RESEARCH TIME AVAILABLE. BUREAU FOR FAR EAST WILL REASSUME CONTRACT MONITORING AND WILL DETERMINE IF CONTRACT (WHICH EXPIRES 6/30/67) SHOULD BE REWRITTEN TO EXPRESS BUREAU'S NEEDS MORE ADEQUATELY. RESEARCH RESULTS, ESPECIALLY IN THE AREA OF REGIONAL ECONOMIC INTEGRATION, WILL BE USED IN FUTURE AID ASSISTANCE PROGRAMS BOTH IN ASIA AND ELSEWHERE.

Abstract: BRIEF SUMMARY REPORT DATED 9/16/66 OF PRELIMINARY DATA REVIEW OF USAID-COMISSIONED OHIO STATE UNIV (OSU) SPECIAL STUDY  TO DETERMINE EFFECTS OF BRAZILIAN FERTILIZER LOAN'S INTERNAL CREDIT SYSTEM (CNCR) ON FERTILIZER USE. UNDER THE LOAN, CREDIT-WORTHY FARMERS RECIEVE FERTILIZER FROM PARTICIPANT DISTRIBUTORS AT A SIZEABLE DISCOUNT CONTINGENT UPON REPAYMENT BY A SPECIFIC DUE DATE. USO TEAM COLLECTED 313 QUESTIONNAIRES FROM FARMERS,BANKS,DISTRIBUTORS,& LOCAL AUTHORITIES IN EIGHT MUNICIPIOS IN STATES OF PARANA,SAO PAULO,AND MINAS GERAIS. 2 FURTHUR MUNICIPIOS ARE SCHEDULED FOR INTERVIEWING AT A LATER DATE. SUMMARY OF PRELIMINARY DATA IS SUBJECT TO COMPLETE ANALYSIS AT OSU. RESULTS OF SURVEY INDICATE THAT DISCOUNT PROVISION SERVED THE DUAL PURPOSE OF OFFERING SUBSTANTIAL PRICE REDUCTION WHILE ENSURING PROMPT REPAYMENT AT THE RISK OF FORFEITING THE DISCOUNT. THIS DISCOUNT PROVISION APPEARS TO BE ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT FACTORS IN THE CREDIT SYSTEM'S SUCCESS. MOST PARTICIPATING FARMERS HAD USED BOTH CREDIT & FERTILIZER PREVISOUSLY,THOUGH THERE WERE A CONSIDERABLE NUMBER OF IRST-TIMERS IN MINAS GERIAIS AND A SMALLER NUMBER IN PARANA.THE TIGHTENING OF CREDIT BY TRADITIONAL SOURCES OF FINANCING DURING 1965 MUST BE TAKEN INTO ACCOUNT IN MEASURING THE IMPACT OF THE CNCR PROGRAM UPON FERTILIZER CONSUMPTION. FARMERS GENERALLY FOUND THE PROGRAM TO HAVE BEEN THE BEST AVAILABLE TO THEM; IT WAS DEEMED LESS BUREAUCRATIC,WITH NO DELAY IN RECEIVING THE FERTILIZER,AND NO INSPECTION OF LOAN-RELATED ACTIVITIES. ON THE OTHER HAND,THE INFLEXIBILITY OF THE REPAYMENT SCHEDULE DID NOT TAKE INTO ACCOUNT PRODUCTION & MARKETING PROBLEMS THAT COULD AFFECT FARMER'S RESOURCES. FARMERS WITH PREVIOUS FERTILIZING EXPERIENCE ARE LIKELY TO APPLY MORE PER LAND UNIT; THERE IS WIDESPREAD BELIEF THAT FERTILIZER USE AUGMENTS PRODUCTION BY MORE THAN 50%. USAGE IS HAMPERED BY A LACK OF SOIL ANALYSIS DATA; THE MINAS GERAIS DISTRIBUTOR DID,HOWEVER,OFFER SOIL TESTING SERVICES. WITHOUT LOAN INSPECTION,THE POTENIIAL DOES EXIST FOR MISUSE OF LOAN FUNDS BY FARMERS OR DISTRIBUTORS.

Abstract: EVALUATES PROJECT PERFORMANCE FROM 4/63 TO 9/66. PROJECT OBJECTIVE IS TO DEVELOP IMPROVED VARIETIES OF MAIZE, SORGHUM, AND MILLET ADAPTED TO AFRICAN CONDITIONS AND TO IMPROVE METHODS OF CULTIVATION. WORK IS BEING DONE IN NIGERIA, UGANDA, AND KENYA. UNDER A PASA WITH USAID, THE US DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE HAS PROVIDED A TEAM OF SCIENTISTS OF EXTREMELY HIGH CALIBRE. IMPROVED STRAINS OF SORGHUM EXHIBITING YIELD INCREASES OF 20% AND OVER HAVE BEEN OBTAINED. SEVERAL THOUSAND NURSERY AND YIELD TEST PLOTS ARE DEVOTED TO TESTING THESE VARIETIES FOR LOCAL ADAPTATION. A PROGRAM HAS BEEN STARTED FOR DEVELOPMENT OF MALE STERILE SORGHUM LINES AND FERTILITY RESTORING LINES FOR THE PRODUCTION OF HYBRIDS. THE WORLD SORGHUM COLLECTION (5000 VARIETIES) IS BEING GROWN AND EVALUATED FOR RESISTANCE TO DISEASES AND INSECTS. THE WORLD MILLET COLLECTION (OVER 2000 VARIETIES) HAS BEEN GROWN IN OBSERVATION PLOTS. THE MORE PROMISING LINES ARE BEING EVALUATED FOR YIELD, INSECT AND DISEASE RESISTANCE, AND OTHER DESIRABLE AGRONOMIC CHARACTERISTICS AND ARE BEING INCREASED AND TESTED IN THE REGIONS. THE MOST DISEASE RESISTANT LINES ARE BEING CROSSED WITH ADAPTED TYPES TO COMBINE DISEASE RESISTANCE AND HIGH YIELD. COVENTIONAL DOUBLE-CROSS HYBRIDS (INVOLVING FOUR INBRED LINES) WERE USED AT THE START OF THE MAIZE PROGRAM, BUT NOW INTER-VARIETAL HYBRIDS (CROSSES BETWEEN TWO VARIETIES, TWO HYBRIDS, OR A VARIETY AND A HYBRID) DEVELOPED FROM SOME OF THE BETTER LOCAL VARIETIES AND A CENTRAL AMERICAN VARIETY ARE YIELDING 50% TO 100% MORE THAN THE LOCAL VARIETIES,COMPARED TO A 25% TO 30% INCREASE IN YIELD FOR THE CONVENTIONAL HYBRIDS. CONTINUED SELECTION WITHIN THE PARENT VARIETIES SHOULD FURTHER INCREASE THE YIELDS OF THE INTER-VARIETAL HYBRIDS DEVELOPED DURING THE NEXT FEW YEARS. INTER-VARIETAL CROSSES ACCOUNT FOR THE BULK OF THE HYBRID MAIZE SEED NOW BEING SOLD IN KENYA. THE HYBRID MAIZE SEED PROGRAM IN KENYA IS UNIQUE IN THAT SEED IS SOLD AS A PART OF A "PACKAGE" WHICH INCLUDES FERTILIZER, PLANT PROTECTION AND IMPROVED CULTURAL PRACTICES. THIS HAS CAUSED THE FARMERS TO RECIEVE VERY HIGH YIELDS AND HAS LED TO ACCEPTANCE OF HYBRID MAIZE AS A "NEW CROP."

Abstract: EVALUATES USAID ASSISTANCE TO THE GOVT OF THE PHILIPPINES FROM 9/1/66-9/30/66 TO UNDERTAKE SURVEYS AND STUDIES PREPARATORY TO THE FORMULATION OF COMPREHENSIVE DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS FOR THE NATION'S SEVEN MAJOR RIVER BASINS. COMMENTS ON THE PRELIMINARY REPORT ON THE CENTRAL LUZON BASIN WERE RECEIVED SEPT 10. THE FEASIBILITY REPORT ON THE UPPER PAMPANGA RIVER PROJECT WAS DELIVERED TO USAID AND THE GOP ON 9/28/77. REPORTS FOR THE CAGAYAN AND COTABATO BASINS AND DRAFTS OF PRELIMINARY REPORTS FOR THE AUGSAN AND BICOL RIVER BASINS ARE IN REPRODUCTION. A DRAFT REPORT ON THE ILOG-HILABANGAN RIVER BASIN IS IN PROGRESS. THE AERO SERVICE CORP CONTINUED THE TOPOGRAPHIC MAP AND MOSAIC WORK UNDER ITS CONTRACT WITH THE US BUREAU OF RECLAMATION. ALL MOSAICS HAVE EITHER BEEN ACCEPTED OR ARE IN THE FINAL STAGES OF CORRECTION.

Abstract: Evaluates performance of the Robert R. Nathan Advisory Group (NAG) in a project to improve economic development planning in Korea. Evaluation covers the period 11/01/65 to 7/31/66, and is based on standard audit procedures. A review of time, leave, and attendance records through 7/31/66 indicated that the contractor provided personnel in the categories required by the contract.  Records for 8/66 had been sent to the contractor's home office.  Auditors recommend that AID/W include these records in its audit of the home office. Secretarial services of an American citizen were provided on a local hire basis from 10/14/64 to 7/31/65.  The contract provided that the first two months of these services would be reimbursable in local currency, and the remaining months in dollars.  The auditors recommend that AID/W determine if the dollar payments duplicated any local currency payments.  Although the contracts stipulated that the work-week of NAG personnel would conform to the Government of Korea's Economic Planning Board's (EPB) five and one-half day work-week, some of the NAG staff did not work on Saturdays or certain U.S. holidays.  However, on 7/14/66, the USOM Contract Representative officially approved the practice, with the written concurrence of the EPB contract representative.  The total dollar obligation for the NAG contract (AID-fe-82) is $728,760.  AID/W payments to NAG through 7/31/66 totaled $475,413.

Abstract: 5/13/64-5/9/66. AUTHOR'S COMMENTS ON PROJECT ACTIVITY, PRIMARILY THE NORTHEAST BRAZIL HIGHWAY CONSTRUCTION LOAN AND ON PROJECTS IN CEARA AND RIO GRANDE NORTE: 1. BRAZILIAN HIGHWAY ENGINEER ORGANIZATIONS AND CONSTRUCTION CONTRACTORS LACK COMPETENT, EXPERIENCED STAFF, FUNDS, MODERN EQUIPMENT. 2. BECAUSE STATE SALARY SCALES ARE SO LOW, ENGINEERS ARE UNDERSTAFFED AND UNAVAILABLE FOR NEEDED FIELD EXPERIENCE. LOW SALARIES RESULT IN SUBSTANDARD PRODUCTS AND MAINTENANCE. 3. SUB-PROFESSIONAL TECHNICAL PERSONNEL FOR SURVEY, DESIGN, MATERIALS TESTING AND CONSTRUCTION INSPECTION ARE IN SHORT SUPPLY. UNSKILLED LABOR IS IN OVER-SUPPLY. 4. DELAY IN SELECTION OF CONSULTANT RESULTED IN STATES INITIALLY LIMITING FUNDS, POOR WORKMANSHIP, LACK OF PRELIMINARY SOILS AND MATERIALS TESTING. 5.WHEN CONSULTANT WAS AVAILABLE, WORK PROGRESSED FAIRLY RAPIDLY. 6. DEALING WITH THE SUPERINTENDENCY FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE NORTHEAST (SUDENE) INVOLVED DEALING WITH A CUMBERSOME ADMINISTRATIVE/LEGAL SUPERSTRUCTURE. 7. NEGOTIATING A CONSULTANT CONTRACT WAS THE MAJOR PROBLEM AND CHIEF CAUSE OF DELAY; AS SUDENE APPEARED UNWILLING OR UNABLE TO DO THIS AND AID AND BUREAU OF PUBLIC ROADS STAFF DRAFTED LETTERS, TRANSLATED PROCEDURES INTO PORTUGUESE, EXPLAINED METHODS OF RATING CONSULTANTS, PRESENTED SAMPLE CONTRACTS TO HELP. LACK OF LEGAL ADVISOR CAUSED IMPASSES. AID/W RESOLVED DIFFICULTY OF NO PERFORMANCE BONDS BY ISSUING A WAIVER. AID/RIO LEGAL STAFF ASSISTED USA CONTRACTORS BIDDING PROCEDURES. RECOMMENDATIONS: 1. AVOID DEALING WITH SUDENE. USE STATE AND LOCAL AGENCIES. 2. PROVIDE MORE LEGAL ASSISTANCE FOR ENGINEERS. 3. ASK GOB FOR SPECIFIC GUIDELINES ON DETAILS OF TAX AND CUSTOMS. 4. AVOID FINANCIAL ADVANCES ON FUTURE CONSTRUCTION WHICH MAY NOT MEET SPECIFICATIONS. SUMMARY: IN SPITE OF FRUSTRATIONS AND DELAYS, GOB CONSTRUCTION STANDARDS ARE BEING IMPROVED. MISSION COMMENTS: AGREES WITH DOWNING ANALYSIS EXCEPT FOR HIS OVER-CRITICISM OF SUDENE. ADDS THAT DOWNING ADMITS HE IS NOT AWARE OF ANY ALLEGED EVIDENCE OF "GRAFT" AS STATED IN HIS REPORT.

Abstract: GOVERNMENT OF KOREA FINANCED INTERCEPTOR SEWER SYSTEM WHILE AID FUNDED CONSTRUCTION OF SEWAGE TREATMENT PLANT. PROJECT GOALS WERE REMOVAL OF 80% BIOCHEMICAL OXYGEN DEMAND AND SETTLEABLE SOLIDS FROM WASTE PRIOR TO DISPOSAL INTO HAN RIVER. LACK OF SEPARATE STORM & SANITARY SEWERS HAS CAUSED FLOW OF MORE THAN TWICE THE PLANT'S DAILY CAPACITY, WITH THE RESULT THAT EXCESS IS PASSED UNTREATED INTO THE HAN. ALTHOUGH OPERATING PROPERLY AT PROJECT END, PLANT ABLE TO TREAT LESS THAN 40% OF SEWAGE ORIGINATING IN PLANNED SERVICE AREA. SITUATION EXACERBATED BY LACK OF PLANS FOR SANITARY COLLECTION SEWERS & UNEXPECTED POPULATION GROWTH IN SERVICE AREA. NIGHT SOIL TREATMENT BEING APPLIED TO RELIEVE OVERBURDENING OF PLANT.

Abstract: LOAN TO THE CORPORACION MINERA DE BOLIVIA (COMIBOL) FOR THE 3RD & FINAL PHASE OF A MULTI-DONOR (AID, INTER-AMERICAN DEVELOPMENT BANK-IDB, FED REP OF GERMANY) PROGRAM TO INCREASE THE COST-EFFECTIVENESS OF COMIBOL'S MINING, MILLING & ADMIN OPERATIONS AND THEREBY INCREASE ITS PRODUCTION OF METALS, PARTICULARLY TIN.PROJECT CONSISTS OF 6 COMPONENTS: 1) MINERAL EXPLORATION-THIS PHASE CONTINUES EFFORTS INITIATED UNDER PHASED I & II WHICH INCLUDE GEOPHYSICAL & GEOCHEM EXPLORATION, DIAMOND DRILLING, EXCAVATION. 16 GEOLOGISTS WILL BE RETAINED IN THE FIELD TO DIRECT THIS EXPLORATION. 2) MINE DEVELOPMENT-NEW SHAFTS WILL BE SUNK IN 7 OF THE EXISTING MINES & NEW TUNNELS DUG IN SEVERAL OTHERS. A US CONSULTANT WILL PLAN DESIGNS FOR NEW MINING PLANTS AND IMPROVEMENTS TO EXISTING PLANTS. 3) METALLURGICAL RESEARCH-RESRCH WILL CONTINUE DURING THIS PHASE ON METHODS TO IMPROVE RECOVERY OF METALS FROM ORES. 4) MILL EXPANSION & IMPRVMNT-CONCENTRATORS AT 4 COMIBOL MINES WILL BE MODIFIED TO RECEIVE A GREATER CAPACITY AND/OR VARIETY OF ORES. 5) COMBINED LAY-OFF & COMMISSARY SUPPLY PROGRAM-PROJ FUNDS PROVIDE COMMISSARY SUPPLIES WHICH ARE SOLD TO GENERATE CAPITAL FOR COMPENSATION OF LAID-OFF WORKERS. UP TO 4800 ARE EXPECTED TO BE LAID OFF UNDER COMIBOL WORK FORCE REDUCTION PROGRAM. 6) TECH & ADMIN REORGANIZATION-24 HIGHLY-QUALIFIED TECH PERSNNL WILL BE RECRUITED TO FILL MGMT & TECH POSITIONS WITHIN COMIBOL. THIS GROUP WOULD CONSIST OF METALLURGISTS, MINING ENGINEERS, A MECH & AN ELECT ENG, GEOLOGIST, COMPTROLLER & FOUNDRYMAN. AID LOAN FUNDS WOULD BE LIMITED TO PAYMENT OF SALARIES OF US CITIZENS EMPLOYED. AN ADVISORY GROUP OF 5 PROFESSIONALS EXPERIENCED IN MINING CO MGMT WILL PREPARE OR APPROVE PLANS FOR COMIBOL TECH & ADMIN REORG, ADVISE COMIBOL MGMT IN ALL AREAS OF ITS OPERATIONS, APPROVE PROCUREMENTS AND SUPERVISE EXCUTION OF ALL PLANS & PROCRMNT, AND PROVIDE METALLURGY & FINANCE ACCNTNG SRVCS. Abstract: Evaluates proj performance from 11/62 through 1/66.  Purpose of proj is to increase Burma's teak production through upgrading (re-equipping) several teak extraction & milling facilities.  Eval was conducted by reviewing proj reports and making on-site inspections. Proj objectives were not achieved due largely to the shortcomings of the principal contractor for the sawmilling machinery, the NE Ohio Machine Builders, Inc. (NOMB).  NOMB did not meet eqpmnt deliv deadlines and those shipments received were sometimes incomplete or contained erroneous items. Some key eqpmnt & parts were 18 months delinquent in arriving.  As a result, full installation of eqpmnt could probably not be accomplished until late 1966.  Had AID not been limited to selecting a contractor able to provide eqpmnt according to foreign specs, these contractor problems could possibly have been avoided.  Util of such a contractor was necessitated by the use of designs & bidding specs which had been prepared earlier under the auspices of the UN (the then anticipated implementing agent). Instead of equipping 5 sawmills as planned, proj commodities were divided among only 3. This alteration in proj design was cited as justified inasmuch as some of the mills were adjacent to each other and it seemed more desirable to develop one large operation in a given area rather than two smaller ones.  As this change in the workplan was executed through only a verbal agreement, it is recommended that the Proj Agreement be formally amended to comply with this change. The following recommendations are suggested:  1) the State Timber Board (STB) and the proj coordinator should maintain a closer liaison with the contractor concerning equipment shortages; 2) the STB & proj coordinator should insure that AID emblems are affixed on all AID-financed commodities (much of the equipment was not so marked); 3) proj coord should attempt to ascertain the GOB's contribution to this proj; 4) as there was a lack of sufficient documentation on the status of the proj, proj coordinators should submit regular progress reports providing such information.

Abstract: This report summarizes the most widely applicable findings and action recommendations derived from a series of 30 coordinated country studies of A.I.D.'s participant training program. Principal recommendations are that: (1) participants should be involved in planning their own program; (2) supervisors should be involved in selecting trainees and in planning both their program and the use to which the training will be put; (3) except where professional reasons indicate otherwise, longer-term training should be preferred to short-term training; (4) USAID and the host government should make formulate definite plans up front of how returned trainees will be employed; (5) steps should be taken to ensure that participants are informed about and satisfied with their programs prior to their departure; and (6) follow-up activities with participants, particularly their contacts with USAID, should be increased. (Author abstract, modified)

Abstract: PROJECT DEVELOPS AND EVALUATES METHODS TO REDUCE NUTRIENT LOSS/FOOD WASTE RESULTING FROM INTESTINAL DISEASE PREVALENT IN UNDERDEVELOPED COUNTRIES. PARTICULAR ATTENTION TO INTERACTION BETWEEN ENVIRONMENTAL SANITATION, GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT DISEASES, TROPICAL MALABSORPTION. PROJECT CONDUCTED 4 PHASES: 1.REVIEW OF RELEVANT LITERATURE; 2.PILOT TESTS OF METHODOLOGY; 3.DISSEMINATION OF DEVELOPED METHODOLOGY; 4.APPLICATION OF DEVELOPED METHODS IN SEVERAL REPRESENTATIVE UNDERDEVELOPED COUNTRIES WHERE THIS HEALTH PROBLEM MOST PREVALENT. ANTICIPATED RESULT-METHODOLOGY TO DETERMINE COST EFFECTIVENESS OF IMPROVED ENVIRONMENTAL SANITATION LEADING TO REDUCED GASTROINTESTINAL DISEASE/IMPROVED FOOD ABSORPTION/LESS FOOD WASTE.

Abstract: LOAN PROVIDED TO THE CAMPANHIA CENTRAL BRASILERIRA DE FORCAELETRICA (CCBFE) TO ASSIST IN FINANCING THE CONSTRUCTION OF A 115 MW HYDROELECTRIC PLANT AT MASCARENHAS ON THE LOWER DOCE RIVER, ABOUT 300 MILES NORTHEAST OF RIO DE JANEIRO, BRAZIL.LOAN WILL ALSO SUPPORT CCBFE'S PROGRAM TO EXPAND AND MODERNIZE ITS TRANSMISSION AND DISTRIBUTION SYSTEMS. THE POWERHOUSE WILL BE DESIGNED FOR FOUR 38.5 MW KAPLIN TURBINE GENERATOR UNITS WITH THREE UNITS INSTALLED INITIALLY AS PART OF THIS PROJECT. THE DAM WILL BE MADE OF CONCRETE THROUGHOUT. IT WILL BE 625 METERS LONG AND HAVE A MAXIMUM HEIGHT OF 28 METERS. A STEP-UP SUBSTATION WILL BE BUILT ON THE RIVER BANK IMMEDIATLEY UPSTREAM FROM THE DAM. THE TRANSMISSION AND DISTRIBUTION PROGRAM WILL INCLUDE CONSTRUCTION OF NEW TRANSMISSION LINES AND SUBSTATIONS; IMPROVEMENTS TO EXISTING LINES; IMPROVEMENT AND EXPANSION OF EXISTING SUBSTATIONS; PLUS OVERHAUL AND EXPANSION OF THE DISTRIBUTION SYSTEMS IN THE CITIES OF CARAPINA, SERRA, PRAIA, VITORIA, CACHOEIRO DO STAPEMIREM, VILAVELHA, CARIACICA, AND OTHER COMMUNITIES. THE SYSTEM FREQUENCY WILL BE CONVERTED FROM 50 CYCLES TO BRAZIL'S STANDARDIZED 60 CYCLES. A NEW COMMUNICATIONS SYSTEM WILL BE INCLUDED FOR THE POWER STATIONS, HEADQUARTERS, AND KEY SUBSTATIONS. IN ADDITION, EQUIPMENT FOR THE GENERAL MANAGEMENT AND OPERATIONS OF THE SYSTEM, LABORATORY APPARATUS, SPECIAL TOOLS, VEHICLES, AND A TRAINING PROGRAM FOR CCBFE PERSONNEL WILL BE PROVIDED. THE LOAN WILL FINANCE ALL US DOLLAR COSTS OF THE PROJECT WHICH INCLUDE THE IMPORTED GENERATING AND ELECTRICAL EQUIPMENT AND MATERIALS AS WELL AS US CONSULTING ENGINEERING SERVICES. THE PROJECT WILL PROVIDE THE ENERGY BASE WHICH WILL MAKE POSSIBLE A SIGNIFICANT INDUSTRIAL EXPANSION IN THE STATE OF ESPIRITO SANITO.

Abstract: LOAN TO GOVT OF PERU WILL FINANCE CONSTRUCTION AND REPAIR OF ELECTRIC GENERATION, TRANSMISSION AND DISTRIBUTION FACILITIES NECESSARY TO ELECTRIFY AN AREA OF APPROX 216 SQ MI. FUNDS WILL BE SUB-LENT TO COOPERATIVA ELECTRICA COMUNAL DEL CENTRO, LDTA, A LOCAL COOP IN THE MANTARO VALLEY. SERVICIOS ELECTRICOS NATIONALES (SEN) WILL OPERATE AND MAINTAIN 3 HYDROELECTRIC POWER PLANTS PRODUCING 5410 KW, 42 MILES OF NEW AND EXISTING 33 KV TRANSMISSION LINES AND SUBSTATIONS. TRANSMSSN LINES WILL BE CONSTRCTD FROM THE PLANT UNDER CONSTRCTN AT HUARISCA TO PILCIMAYO AND HUANCAYO, WITH SUBSTATNS AT PILCOMAYO, CHONGAS BAJO, CHUPACA AND HUANCAYO. LINE FROM INGENIO TO HUANCAYO WILL BE REPAIRED. COOPERATIVA WILL OWN, MAINTAIN AND OPERATE A NETWORK OF DISTRIBUTN LINES AND WILL BUY POWER FROM SEN, RELIEVING THE COOP OF RESPONSBLTY FOR THE PLANTS, TRANSMSSN LINES AND SUBSTATNS. DISTRIBUTION SYSTEM VOLTAGE WILL BE 7.2/12.5 KV. SERVICES AND METERS WILL BE PROVIDED TO 10,000 COOP MEMBERS INITIALLY, INCREASING TO 13,000 IN 10 YEARS, INCLUDING COMMERICAL AND INDUSTRIAL CONSUMERS. EVALUATION OF THE POWER NEEDS WILL BE MADE AFTER 5 AND AGAIN AT 10 YEARS TO DETERMINE THE SCHEDULING OF ADDITIONAL POWER NEEDS. NATIONAL RURAL ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE ASSOCIATION (NRECA), AN AMERICAN FIRM, WILL PROVIDE SUCH TECHNICAL AND MANAGEMENT ADVISORY SERVICES TO GOVT OF PERU AS SURVEYS, STUDIES AND SEMINARS. STUDIES ARE NOW UNDERWAY TO FIND SUITABLE POLES FOR ELECTRIC POWER LINES. IMPORTED YELLOW PINE WILL BE USED IN PRIMARY LINES BUT NATIVE, TREATED POLES, POSSIBLY OF THE EUCALYPTUS TREE, WILL BE USED IN THE SECONDARY LINES IF FEASIBLE. OTHER STUDY AREAS INCLUDE ECONOMIC FEASIBILITY, COOP ORGANIZATION, CONDITION OF ELECTRIC GENERATORS AND VOLTAGE REGULATION.
